{"product_id": "208480", "page": 1, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-02-19", "text": "Extremely underrated Assassin's Creed game, the story is very well written with very fun missions, and it is also fun to play as Connor Kenway, because he is more immature than the previous two assassins, Ezio Auditore and Alta\u00efr Ibn-La'Ahad, creating a more unique playthrough. After finishing the long story (which is great) there are many missions to do to expand your village just like \"low budget story missions\" that are pretty fun, along with the collection of items, and hunting too, this game is great. 10/10", "hours": 39.7, "user_id": "76561198313618824", "username": "Truture Funks", "products": 13, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 1, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-02-19", "text": "Assassins Creed 3 was a game happening at the time of the American revolution. The singleplayer was fine but it was too slow at the start, the story was sometimes hard to follow and sadly it only took 9-12 hours to complete. I'm sure you can find an Assassins Creed game with a better singleplayer.\nGraphically they took a big step from they're recent games and the voice acting was incredible very well polished and can still follow up to the graphic on the new releases to this date.\nOne of my best experiences was combat i like how you aren't making the same animation while fighting over and over again but always doing something new.\nThe game didn't have that many bugs like there is in the newer releases of the Assassins Creed games, the riding mechanics is still absolutely trash though and was kinda game breaking in my opinion.\nI recommend buying this game if you cant get it for 8 euros on sale and you are all for the story and ain't caring about stuff like open world, side missions and so on.\n7/10", "hours": 14.9, "username": "Needs", "products": 95, "early_access": false}
