{"product_id": "208480", "page": 2, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-02-13", "text": "Although AC III is not the best AC game made, it is still a decent game with some good improvements in the gameplay such as the fast travel option, the hunting, and the naval missions to name a few. There are definitely some flaws, and the main character might seem a bit dull and stiff after three games with Ezio. However, all things considered, AC III is still a decent game that I spend many hours on, enjoying the story or just exploring the frontier. If you played and liked the other AC games, I'd recommend giving it a try, but if you're new to the franchise, maybe start with a classic like AC II.", "hours": 125.1, "user_id": "76561198227979960", "username": "QuickSilver_1828", "products": 8, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 2, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2018-02-11", "text": "THIS GAME REQUIRES UPLAY, THERE IS NO BENEFIT TO BUYING IT ON STEAM!\nThe physics going nuts was fun at first, but then the not-so-fun glitches started. I encountered 4 crashes to desktops & 3 game breaking glitches that required a restart in the first 8 hours alone. Due to mandatory use of Uplay, the game eventually refused to launch until I completely re-installed uplay. There is no benefit buying this game on Steam and Uplay breaking might prevent you from launching the game altogether.\nBuy this game on console.\n---\nTechnical issues aside the game is pretty decent. Not as good as it's predecessors such as AC2 and Brotherhood, but still a 7/10. Gameplay is good, albeit the controls were tweaked from previous games. Graphics are great, especially for its time, but some of the faces have gone into the uncanny valley. Music is great too, no complaints here. Voice acting is good. Connor is going to be hit or miss for you. He's different than Ezio, more akin to Alta\u00efr.\nMight edit this if my opinion changes after I have finished the game. If I can get the game to launch again...", "hours": 26.4, "username": "Destructive Deer", "products": 117, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 2, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-02-11", "text": "The first AC game that I have played. So enjoyable, has great scenario, even better gameplay, and enough graphics. Our character is Connor Kenway, a charismatic Indian half-blooded assassin. Place is New York and Boston. Time is Indepence War of America. This game is one of the best AC games I think. Buy it I advice.\nGraphics: 90/100\nGameplay: 95/100\nScenario: 85/100\nDetails: 87/100\nGeneral: 89/100", "hours": 4.7, "username": "Ave Deus", "products": 42, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 2, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-02-10", "text": "Not the best AC game (probably my least favourite) but its not a bad game. The story does take a very long time to get started which probably puts a lot of people of, but once you are a few hours in its quite enjoyable. The main story doesn't really start until 5+ hours in and you spend the beginning of the game playing as a different character from the main protagonist which might confuse some people. The main protagonist of the game (Connor) is pretty boring and the American setting is pretty weak by AC standards, but this was also the first AC game to run in a new version of the anvil engine, which brought a lot of new features to the franchise like climbing trees and rocks, better and smoother climbing and better stealth, and future games would not be so good if this game didn't exist. This game has its flaws, but Ubisoft did actually try and innovate this time after 4 previous games with copy and pasted gameplay, animations and sound effects. The modern day in this game is one of the best in the franchise and is a fairly good conclusion to the original story they were trying to tell with Desmond, before ubisoft had to screw it up in later games.\nTo summarise, its not the best game or AC game, but its still fun if you can get past the boring start. If you are new to the franchise then I wouldn't use this game as a starting point but if you are a fan then I would recommend it.", "hours": 51.8, "username": "JonathanWhiting13 Birthday", "products": 796, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 2, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-02-09", "text": "Despite new engine for game (lags for my not too strong laptop) and many negative things in the game, I really enjoyed this game. It is like a breath of the fresh air after the Revelations which came quite boring.\nThe strongest part of the game are, of course, side missions, especially Homestead missions where Connor has emotions and at least some personality. It was really interesting to complete the game on 100%, even collecting collectives was interesting, while in the Revelations I just haven't had any wish to play the game after the last sequence.\nOverall, all Assassin's Creed games are good and Assassin's Creed 3 is not an exception, especially if played in order with other games from the series, so I strongly recommend this game for any AC fan!", "hours": 76.0, "username": "Topic\u2122", "products": 28, "early_access": false}
