{"product_id": "208480", "page": 5, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2018-01-24", "text": "This was a desperate try to \"resuscitate\" whole franchise. It is obvious that no loger are games developed to be of the best quality, but to earn money for the developers. It goes as usual - they see an opportunity to make money and they go for it; so they start making many, so called, brand new games with all the new functions; but all I can see is just the same game (that once was dominant and superb but nowadays no one would even notice it) in a \"brand new\" cloak. Everything remains the same. No spectacular invention. I must admit, though, that the introduction of multiplayer is very nice and I enjoyed playing it. It brings a new point of view to, so called, silent excitement. Final words: mundane, profane, platitude. 3,5/10 (most of the points are for few hours of fun with the multiplayer with friends)", "hours": 64.9, "user_id": "76561198051415187", "username": "Petyr Baelish", "products": 18, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 5, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2018-01-23", "text": "Game is good, when you can actually get it to run properly. Had to go mess around with Nvidia PhysX settings and running the game in compatability mode for windows 7 (I have windows 10) before I could get it to stop crashing. My specs aren't bad either (GTX 970, i7 quad core 4.0Ghz, 16GB RAM, etc.), and I guess it just can't handle newer built PCs? It still freezes randomly and crashes sometimes, and for that I can't recommend this game. It's poorly optimized for mid to high-end PCs. I'm well past the two hour mark as well so I won't be able to refund. If they release a patch that fixes the issues with crashing and freezing, I'll change this review.", "hours": 11.6, "username": "Pyrineer", "products": 156, "early_access": false}
