{"product_id": "208480", "page": 13, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-09", "text": "Its a fun game because of the simple fighting gameplay, the story is rather confusing especially if this is the first time you've tried the series, but that's not my point. The Endings are rather anticlimactic. and the game is not that well-optimized. and there are still a lot of bugs up untill this day.\nIn conclusion if you're just planning to buy a game that has simple mechanics that is excellent in combat, this is the game for you. but if not. then no.", "hours": 24.7, "username": "FlyingShawarmaGuy", "products": 10, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 13, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-08", "text": "One of my favourite this far. I'm at 100% and stopped playing. Free-running in the forest is cool and a great improvement according to the previous games of the series. However there are still many bugs that affects the gameplay. I have rushed through this game to start playing AC IV Black Flag since most of my friends told me that AC IV was better. DON'T..The story stumbles in AC IV so enjoy this game since it has a great storyline with Kenways + Desmond. Read the book while playing if possible. The speeches are 100% the same. After you play a sequence, read the corresponding chapter in the book so you can draw the place in your mind where the events occur.", "hours": 64.9, "username": "Head", "products": 70, "early_access": false}
