{"product_id": "208480", "page": 34, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-08-06", "text": "This is my favorite of the Assassin's Creed series and I put it up there with Red Dead Redemption for open world games. The game does both cities and wilderness very well. The combat is visceral. While the ship content isn't open world, it feels tighter and more epic than the Black Flag ship combat.\nTo me, this feels like the most complete Assassin's Creed experience.\nMy advice to those starting out: The game's intro missions are lengthy and can turn some people off. I would recommend powering through these tutorial missions until the first big turn of events happens. They're great missions for story, but aren't representative of the majority of the game. Stick with it!", "hours": 55.4, "user_id": "76561197970932903", "username": "Cabrien", "products": 680, "early_access": false}
