{"product_id": "208480", "page": 37, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-11", "text": "They finally changed the engine, for one that is absolutely amazing, capable of creating beautiful maps, on the forest or in the cities. The gameplay totally changed, and we forgot about swords and were magnified by Connor's tomahawk. But they forgot one thing, the game carries \"Assassin's Creed\" title, and yet, has nothing to do with the Order of Assassin's. It's just a native who wants revenge on his mother and on his tribe. The story is not all bad, has good characters like Haytham, who tries to make an alliance between templars and assassins. And as i said in my AC Revelations review, from AC III to AC Syndicate, all games shouldn't be bearing the \"Assassin's Creed\" title. The game is about american revolution and that's all. And Connor, untill this day, holds the prize of less carismatic character. It's like they were trying to make you not liking him. The game it's not bad, it's just not an \"Assassin's Creed\" game.\nJust gave an 8 because the new engine who made the game fun to play with the new gameplay and free running trough trees.", "hours": 16.5, "username": "John Winchester", "products": 311, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 37, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-11", "text": "Assassin's Creed III reminds me of the very first game of the series in a few different ways. It seeks to bring something new, but it is a bit unrefined. The story is interesting, but it does drag on in some parts.\nThose things don't detract from the overall experience in my opinion. The new setting is just as captivating as previous ones in it's own way, and the new main character, Connor, is a multi-layered personality, who starts out somewhat arrogant and naive, but by the end, is something more. ACIII also has what seems to me to be the best and most interesting antagonists. This is the first time since the first Assassin's Creed where you might question whether or not the \"villains\" are actually right or not (except ACIII does an even better job of this).", "hours": 45.5, "username": "IronicRobot", "products": 164, "early_access": false}
