{"product_id": "208480", "page": 43, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-06-12", "text": "Pros/neutral:\n- The generally boring combat of assassins creed is quite a lot better in this game than in the previous ones.\n- Interesting setting\n- While i hate getting pulled out if the main game to get my butt fisted with lore (aka desmonds story), it's at least not just boring cutscenes now (you actually get to play as desmond)\nCons:\n- Bland characters (Haytham was the only one that i liked)\n- Forgetable story\n- The environments, while pretty and historically interesting, are not suited for a game like this at all.\n- Every problem that plagues all the other AC games too. \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 missions. Boring parkour due to the complete automation. Simplistic combat.\nUbisoft does too little to fix the major flaws of the series, and in the process lose track of some of the things that made the series work in the first place\nVerdict: 4/10", "hours": 7.9, "username": "Intercourse specialist", "products": 153, "early_access": false}
