{"product_id": "208480", "page": 43, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-12", "text": "This game was pretty good with introducing new mechanics, even if it took time to adjust to them. There's a lot of side content to do, but remember it's all optional if you feel suffocated by it. I stopped doing minor side quests because of that, and getting on with the main story felt good. The funny thing is that you could die more easily to being ambushed by a wolf than getting shot 10+ times while running from hordes of guards. If you can look past the terrible optimization of the towns and not the best AIs, this game is solid.", "hours": 30.6, "username": "FireIceBlade", "products": 90, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 43, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-11", "text": "I played this game when it came out in 2012 on the 360, and recently decided to get it again on PC. I had some issues with the camera glitching when I first played it, but after restarting the game it worked completely fine. I've had no issues or glitches with the game and I think it still manages to look beautiful on PC five years later. I might just be a bit sentimental due to this being my first Assassin's Creed game, but I highly recommend this game.", "hours": 11.6, "username": "Pooch", "products": 67, "early_access": false}
