{"product_id": "208480", "page": 44, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-06-06", "text": "I have incredibly mixed feelings about this game. On the one hand it has a great setting with the Revolutionairy War. The great moments of the US struggle for independence are there and you can really feel a part of this era. Furthermore, developing your own village is fun; although the impact could have been improved (and some of the quests are a bit repetitive) all in all it's a great way to expand your influence.\nThe flipside is the incredible amount of bugs. I can't play for more than five minutes without running into one, and some are close to game breaking.\nTake simple movement. When climbing Connor will frequently just refuse to go where I want him to go, which is particularly annoying if you're on a very high spot. My horse would get stuck in rocks, unable to move. Connor would fall through ledges. It's all massively annoying.\nOr suddenly my mini-map only gives me a minute overview, meaning I have no clue where I are, or where I can go to avoid enemies. The only solution is to reboot the game.\nEntering a printer shop, immediately exiting, and having the printer shop somehow changed to a portal to New York (really, don't ask me what happened there). And obviously at the moment a patrol is walking by, so I can start running/fighting again.\nBoarding a ship and mid animation I already have to start over. That's right, the game had me fail a mission before I had even started it.\nThe list goes on, and it is massively frustrating to go through. Completing the game takes perseverence; at some point you just want to see the ending. And it certainly has its moments. But better not to begin at all. Ubisoft should just have delivered a slightly more bugfree game, because clearly spectacle is more important than decent gameplay.", "hours": 34.5, "user_id": "76561197969316316", "username": "Morthill", "products": 286, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 44, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-06-04", "text": "I have many issues with this game. Overall it was unenjoyable to play because:\n1. Controls felt unnatural and bulky. Fighting and shooting felt cumbersome and clunky.\n2. The map was awful. A marker doesn't give you a route like in GTAV, it just tells you how far left to go.\n3. Too many cutscenes. Throughout the game it felt like my character would wake up, walk outside, cutscene, walk to where I was told to go, cutscene. I never felt in control of the game.\n4. A mockery of history. I was looking forward to being immersed in colonial history but the cheesy list of characters made it a bit silly. Kotaku referred to this as also 'Gump'ish.\nI have always had respect for the Assasins Creed series but felt let down by this one.", "hours": 11.7, "username": "Wilbur Cobb", "products": 47, "early_access": false}
