{"product_id": "208480", "page": 56, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-02-10", "text": "One of the oddest Assassin Creed's I've ever played. Ubisoft did something strange with this title, and it always played different for me compared to Assassin's Creed 2, 4 or any of the others. I suppose I should say it felt more personal and depressing in the end, but not in a bad way. It was fairly realistic in how certain characters acted and reacted.\nThis game isn't considered Ubisoft's strongest in the franchise, not by a long shot (I find 4 to be the best thus far, personally), but it does try new things and delivers these new ideas in a unique way. Worth a play through, but obviously with all Ubisoft titles, buy it while it's dirt cheap during a sale.", "hours": 44.6, "username": "Call The Banners", "products": 232, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 56, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-02-09", "text": "This is by far the most visually pleasing game in the assassins creed series.With a wide map and different seasons, it pleases the eyes.\nThe story follows the life of Ratonhaketon.This game is the first in the series that actually made it feel like it was open world.Of course, the others are also open world, but the things you can do are\nthis game however, there are lots of things to do that are interesting, like hunting animals for instance.\nThe difficulty is not hard.It is normal most of the time.Combat mechanisms have been slightly improved.The new animations during fight sequences makes it much more interesting to fight.\nThis is in my opinion very different from the other games in the series, but is is very good nonetheless.", "hours": 9.9, "user_id": "76561198011965365", "username": "Saint Aaron", "products": 1706, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
