{"product_id": "208480", "page": 90, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-23", "text": "Contrary to the gaming lemmings opinion - This is the best Assassins Creed.\nUbi pulled out all of the stops for this one, in contrast to the newer ones. Newer entries are just cookie cutter, assembly line, diluted versions, that have been getting more ridiculous with each incarnation.\nIt has far more nuanced story and characters.\nIt has decent combat (that controls well), a multitude of settings, a multitude of game mechanics that aren't immersion breaking (or ludicrous) & great graphics.\nOverall it's just the most fleshed out AC and doesn't feel as linear, or consolised as the newer ones.", "hours": 114.5, "user_id": "76561198037802287", "username": "PwG", "products": 290, "early_access": false}
