{"product_id": "208480", "page": 102, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-26", "text": "My favorite Assassin's Creed game. The mix of open wilderness and tight city streets was very well done and a great setting. The story was strong in that it wasn't black and white like many other AC games. The main character wasn't perfect, the bad guys weren't all that bad, and the Revolutionary War had plenty of gray moments to make us think. Connor himself is probably my favorite Assassin. He isn't very emotional, but that's representative of his upbringing, and really allows for great moments when he does let lose. AC has always had great animations, but I think this game had the best. Connor was big and powerful, and his weapons and moveset made it show. When it came out I never had problems playing it on PC and to this day I don't know why people thought it was so buggy. I recommend looking up Connor's Epilogue Monologue on YouTube. For some strange reason it was cut, but it's a great wrap to the game and character.", "hours": 88.4, "username": "Ryan", "products": 476, "early_access": false}
