{"product_id": "208480", "page": 104, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-09", "text": "Excellent game, a real improvement over Revelation. The story is engrossing and entertaining. Sure the introduction to the story is a little long, but it is all worth it.", "hours": 43.1, "username": "dcommando", "products": 313, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 104, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-09", "text": "This was the first assassin's creed game i bought and it was awesome i really like that your able to get cheats by playing the game and exploreing", "hours": 90.7, "username": "Mr. Clean", "products": 23, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 104, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-06-09", "text": "Playing Assassin's Creed III is like reading War and Peace as a first grader.\nProfoundly impressive, but pretty much indecipherable.\nIt is my sincere opinion that this is the weakest of all the Assassin's Creed entries. It's hard to deal with, the missions are repetitive, there are fetch quests, and you don't play as the main Assassin until five hours in. The gameplay is somewhat familiar to me, as a veteran player, but it has some very confusing changes to the control scheme.\nHowever, it advances the story. If anything, that is probably the best virtue of the game - it advances the in-game storyline and shows off the AnvilNext engine. Don't think of this as a game, think of it as a very extended tech demo in preparation for Black Flag.", "hours": 114.2, "user_id": "76561198072430311", "username": "Vedrfolnir", "products": 159, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 105, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-08", "text": "AC3 is a pretty solid game. I had enjoyed watching the Assassin's creed storyline before and decided to buy into the AC franchise at AC3 which, many of my friends said was a bad idea and AC3 got bad-mouthed by most of them and internet reviews as one of the lesser of all the AC games. I bought the game on sale anyway and throughly enjoyed every second of the game.\nGranted, there's a few glitches that I experienced and the character of Connor could've been better fleshed out and made in a way that the player could connect to but otherwise the story and gameplay is worth it. I would definitely recommend buying it, particularly if it's on sale as when I got it.\n9/10 Would single-handedly win the American Revolution again.", "hours": 28.9, "username": "iScout", "products": 21, "found_funny": 5, "early_access": false}
