{"product_id": "208480", "page": 110, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-05-04", "text": "It was decent. I really dislike having to gather and craft things in single player games. Probably some MMO\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665on the dev team. Character isn't nearly as cool as Esio. He's actually a pretty big \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665. I personally would have cut George Washington's throat but our \"hero\" \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665es out. If you like the AC series you HAVE to play it, why are you even reading a review?", "hours": 57.7, "username": "Wiz", "products": 1086, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 110, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-05-04", "text": "Assassin's Creed III is very, very bad successor to the second parts... Although, I did not recommend Assassin's Creed Revelations (you can see in my review why), I was pretty much impressed with its gameplay and Ezio as a fantastic character (that he was in whole trilogy)...\nOn the other hand, Assassin's Creed III is bland, it has confusing storyline, irritating main character (I preferred Haytham 10 times more xD), idiotic conversations, even worse storyline in 2012 events (although I never much cared about those in Assassin's Creed series), \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 plot details... It is a complete miss writing-wise... It feels like Ubisoft hired 10 year olds to write story and conversations and general feelings of characters... I was just completely pushed away by all of it during my gameplay...\nAs for the gameplay itself it is pretty much what Assassin's Creed is and was... Nice feel and easy combat, a lot of climbing and jumping and exploring a world... Nice addition (that, as I heard is perfected in Black Flag) is naval combat that feels nice and interesting... And new, in a game that definitely needed something new...\nShort version:\nPros:\n- Assassin's Creed, as it is... (If you like it that way :))\n- Naval Combat\nCons:\n- Confusing storyline\n- Irritating main character\n- Very bad conversations\n- Even worse plot detail fails...\nIf you generally like Assassin's Creed (like I do), you should play it... Just to wrap up everything... If you don't like Assassin's Creed this is definitely not the one that will make you like it. So, it's a Thumbs horizontal from me, but a little bit more to the down, because I just didn't enjoy it, although I like the series...", "hours": 21.7, "username": "Balder", "products": 1183, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 110, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-05-02", "text": "AC3 doesn't get the credit it deserves. Connor is one of the best characters I have ever played as in a video game; Ezio had his charm, but Connor has depth and has real character development. The story is enticing, and AC3 has complex and heartfelt themes around father son relationships, and of course if the assassins are in reality the good guys, and the templars the 'evil' ones.  The graphics aren't groundbreaking but are better than if Bethesda had tried to make it... (No offense, I love the Fallout series and Skyrim is amazing) The combat is not hard, but it is very satisfying and is much easier than the sh*t stain Unity's combat was. (Honestly what was Ubisoft thinking...) Try this game out at least, if it isn't your thing, then there's always the refund option.", "hours": 13.5, "username": "Star_Killer", "products": 102, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
