{"product_id": "208480", "page": 130, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-01-10", "text": "Guys i really would not buy this game if i was you,unless you have a monster of a pc cuz when you get to boston your fps cant go over 20.My pc is quire powerfull here are my specs\n8 GB RAM\ni7 @ 3 Ghz\nnVidia GTX470 Display card\nDX 11 compatible souund card", "hours": 1.8, "user_id": "76561198201911887", "username": "Matchstick", "products": 85, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 130, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-10", "text": "I have a weakness for AAA stealth-em-ups, and i've enjoyed the Assassin's Creed series since it started. It's not an amazing series, but it can be fun if you like open-world games and sneaking around.\nIf you were to ask me if this is where you should start the series, I would give you a resounding 'no'. The pace isn't very good, combat is way too easy, and the cities are kinda boring. That said, it's my second favorite game in the series. I love the Colonial setting and hunting. I study Appalachian history and culture, so the setting really strikes a chord with me. Once you get into the right mindset it's a really good game to mess around in, just not as good as AC4 or AC2. Overall, it's just decent.\nHardware wise, it runs fine. I have a Phenom II X4 820 / R9 380X / 16GB RAM and it runs at a pretty high FPS. Tends to stay at 60 when i'm messing around. I may not have much gametime on it ATM but i've played it a lot on console.", "hours": 39.9, "username": "leon14344", "products": 269, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 130, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-01-10", "text": "It took me 3 tries to get past the damn intro.\nAlso, my DLC doesn't work.\nMy only option to use the DLC is to pirate the whole game.\nLet me repeat that, I have to pirate a game I own, just so the DLC I own will work.", "hours": 0.9, "username": "NightBlader", "products": 587, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 130, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-01-10", "text": "Just a rehashed game with new cities.  The only thing great and fun about this game is the naval battles,  It is more or less the same game as the previous ones except with a downgrade in gameplay and story.  I thought the combat was clunky and the cutscenes/story were poorly done.  For me it was the nail in the coffin for this series. I would only recommend this to a huge fan of the franchise, otherwise, it should be avoided.", "hours": 56.5, "user_id": "76561197970408117", "username": "howmaster", "products": 44, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 130, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-09", "text": "Do you like running around and stabbing filthy redcoats in the neck?\nDo you, perhaps like to set traps and go hunting in the wild hours at a time to make a few coins?\nDo you love runnning your own settlement and earning people trust and respect?\nDo you like to have pirate ship battles?\nThen this game is for you, because if has all of that and more. I can't think fo the countless hours I have soent hunting a deer or a fox and selling them. I have so much fun hunting and climbing trees and killing redcoats and finding cool new places, and meeting historical people I have only read and learned about.\nThis game was truly an amazing experience.", "hours": 37.7, "username": "Goon", "products": 56, "early_access": false}
