{"product_id": "208480", "page": 137, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-12-26", "text": "If you've played an assassin's creed game, you pretty much know what you're in for.  The addition of ship-ship  combat is very fun, though.  Arguably more fun than the rest of game.  Alot of grief has been given for Connor's \"boring\" character.  But I actually liked how he was written.  He's more interesting than Altair, and leagues more interesting than Desmond.  The game controls very fluidly, howevery sometimes it is overly sensitive.  I've accidently jumped off a building isntead of parkouring to the next many times.  I did not run into any bugs, and the game runs very well on my five year old laptop.  I would definitely recommend this game, but only if it's on sale.", "hours": 51.7, "user_id": "76561198047852159", "username": "Rashed", "products": 104, "early_access": false}
