{"product_id": "208480", "page": 166, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-08-31", "text": "I am a pretty big fan of the Assassin's Creed series, and I thought ACIII was one of the best out there. It had many hours of good quality gameplay (graphics, plot, freedom as to where you can go, etc.), and the multiplayer option was fun too. I have ACV, and ACIII was MUCH better compared to ACV (thanks a lot bugs :P). ACIII also kept the Desmond Miles plot going in the background, which I like since it sticks to the original idea of the series. I would recommend this game to anyone who doesn't mind a bit  of blood and a lot of fun.", "hours": 43.5, "user_id": "76561198053790182", "username": "wecanrock1", "products": 77, "early_access": false}
