{"product_id": "208480", "page": 168, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-08-22", "text": "Assassin's Creed III, one of the best games in the open world in the history of one of the most complete fighters and simply one of the most beautiful games of this generation.\nThe history of Assassin's Creed III is devoted to the war for the independence of the American colonies. American History - definitely the most intense and interesting. Colonial houses and towers, guns, cocked, Benjamin Franklin - add up to a compelling historical novel.\nAssassin's Creed III - is the pinnacle of the series Assassin's Creed and certainly the best part of it.", "hours": 121.5, "user_id": "76561198086726732", "username": "Dalumba", "products": 161, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 168, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-08-22", "text": "AC 3 is one of the better games in the series, maybe because it walks away from the Italian setting for a breeze of fresh air. The setting and story is compelling, and coupled with the Tyranny of George Washington DLC brings it all to a very nice rounded end. Musical score in this one also adds much to the atmosphere.\nHave to note that in grand digusting Ubisoft style, Episode 1 of the DLC has a game halting bug that hasn't been fixed since its release several years ago. There are long winded fixes to the bug that requires a restart of the DLC. However if you do encounter the bug I would suggest just watching a Youtube playthrough of the last small piece of episode 1 where the bug is, then just start episode 2 and continue.\nDont let it stop you though, as its a fine story!", "hours": 53.0, "username": "Primeh", "products": 735, "early_access": false}
