{"product_id": "208480", "page": 169, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-08-20", "text": "This game is overall good but you'd be better off buying it on console due to the poor optimization on PC.\n\n-Pros:\n-Decent Story\n-Naval Warfare\n-Better Combat than AC2\n-Immersive Environments\n-Cons:\n-Terrible Mission Design\n-Poor Optimization\n-Lots of Bugs", "hours": 10.7, "username": "Jomes", "products": 334, "found_funny": 9, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 169, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-08-18", "text": "I thought the story was a great 20 hours. Of course, the Desmond parts were fairly boring compared to being an Assassin badass. Nonetheless, I seem to be having more fun with the game after I've compelted the main story, and roam around, tearing everybody apart :)\nThe PC requirements for this one are low, at least compared to this game's successor, Black Flag.\nInteresting setup, fun gameplay, but a slow story which drags out a little and leaves you confused at points (there are several plot holes).", "hours": 29.0, "username": "Jackmerius Tacktheritrix", "products": 39, "early_access": false}
