{"product_id": "208480", "page": 171, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-08-10", "text": "Okay Ubisoft, you bunch of geniuses. So the story here is I boot up the game, a Uplay launcher pops up and ask for a signup/login thing. I was like, \"One of these. eh. Fine then\" and create an account. Guess what happens. The launcher crashes. And every time that I've started it since. WHY is there a launcher that requires a password, and does this game even have online stuff to justify having one?\nAlso , HOW do you even f*ck that up?\nI bought FF7 on Steam a while ago, cuz why not. That thing is even more haphazardly thrown together and requires a password and serves no purpose, but guess what, it doesn't friggin' crash when I try to use it.\nI spammed that thing until I got enough gametime to write this to just let the salt out.", "hours": 0.1, "user_id": "76561198084222495", "username": "Klimber", "products": 84, "early_access": false}
