{"product_id": "208480", "page": 184, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-24", "text": "While I personally enjoy this game to some extent, it is not for everybody. What threw off most people is how slow the game is for the first 3-4 hours. It does pick up after that, but a lot of your time is spent running around from cutscene to cutscene with an action setpiece every now and then. While I personally am a fan of more storydriven cinematic games, don't play this game if you want non-stop action-packed assassin awesomeness. Go play Black Flag if you want that.\nAs for the story itself, its good. It tells a personal story of Connor, and there is a lot of development in the characters of Achilles and the villains. However, Connor himself is a very boring and uninteresting protagonist. The combat is good, but very easy. All you have to do is counter, break defense, and then kill.\nOverall, I would recommend this game if you enjoy a very immersive world, and good story, if a bit slow moving.", "hours": 37.8, "username": "Cabbages", "products": 199, "early_access": false}
