{"product_id": "208480", "page": 184, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-06-24", "text": "Oh dear God. The pacing. So. Bloody. Slow. It's like watching a snail creep through molasses. I've so far played the game for close to seven hours and this is how I've spent my time: 50% watching cutscenes, 30% running or walking from point A to point B (seriously, why do I have to walk such long distances? It's neither exciting nor fun), 10% fighting (which is fun, granted), and 10% waiting for the Native American dialogue to be over since I've already read the subtitles five friggin times.\nThe story is, well, kinda standard, I guess, nothing special.... whatever, I don't care anymore. It just takes too damn long to go anywhere. I will probably spend some more hours playing this for reasons passing understanding. Perhaps I have masochistic tendencies. Who knows, really.", "hours": 10.0, "user_id": "76561197972253571", "username": "acowsezmoo", "products": 61, "early_access": false}
