{"product_id": "208480", "page": 190, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-12", "text": "Pros: Smooth combat and graphics\nCons: repetitive and a little too long for what it is\nIf you're a fan of AC games before or after this one you probably will like this one too. AC3 is a solid game but it has it's issues. Without getting nitpicky with the various bugs and glitches that may or may not still be in the game, my biggest gripe was that it lacked innovation. That's mostly okay because the AC series has a winning formula to keep us playing. The contribution that it makes to the series story is like the other games: at the beginning and the end. The middle part is mostly all about the smooth gameplay with some forgetable plot that relates to the period in which it's set. The develops did try to add in a new feature of managing a \"homestead\". Pretty much just a lame crafting and farming system. There's plenty of side objectives in this game but for me I didn't really bother unless they were in my way because it wasn't all that rewarding. Overall a great game with just some minor flaws.\n8.5/10", "hours": 8.7, "user_id": "76561198038375602", "username": "Rammbone", "products": 128, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 190, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-06-12", "text": "Gotta say, I was deeply disappointed with this game. I bought and played Assassin's Creed 4, and I loved it, so then I bought this. A lot of it seemed like it didn't really work, and for most of it you just run back and forth without a real purpose. Even the plot never really had me. I was more interested in played as the bad guy at the beginning than playing as the main character. 3/10 Would never play again.", "hours": 33.5, "username": "Steely Alpha", "products": 324, "early_access": false}
