{"product_id": "208480", "page": 194, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-06", "text": "This is my first AC so I'll keep this reveiw short until I have completed the game (If I ever do)\nPros:\nGood graphics\nGood voice acting\nAnimation is nice\nYou can skip some of the animations\nThere is open world\nLots of parkour\nCons:\nLots of bugs\nSometimes missions are boring and continuous\nIt has Uplay launcher\nSo thats it so far but I will edit this soon", "hours": 8.1, "user_id": "76561198156122013", "username": "\u2605\u265bFlyMo\u265b\u2605", "products": 197, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 194, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-06", "text": "~LIKES~\nGraphics\nStory\nCraft\nReal-life history - For those like me hate reading and lack knowledge of history, but like playing games, then I recommend AC series lol\nInteractives - Riot, free-run buildings,\nWild hunting\nFun killing guards and execute animations\nPlaying as Desmond - I loved playing as Desmond on Brazil and saving his father.\nDifferent maps! - Frontier, New York and Boston\nMostly inspires half of my life\nSmart allies and enemies - Actually knows how to parkour and follow than any other game\nSoundtrack\nHaytham and Connor life\n~DISLIKES~\nUplay\nUnkillable civilians :(\nSame mechanics\nLimited firearms\nMultiplayer\nCitizens ridicolous moving around in cutscenes\nAt the end of the day, I still like the game, I think it's better than all AC series out there.", "hours": 8.0, "username": "Dethrune52", "products": 196, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 194, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-06", "text": "The game generally has a different feel from the previous games (I have the Ezio trilogy on XBox), however, it has not deviated much from the former &quot\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665rape\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665quot; combat of the games after Brotherhood. It's almost sad how much fun the combat is in this game. While the difficulty is absolutely pathetic, any scrub can finish it, it's still a ton of fun spamming the counter button and seeing you decimate everything in a 5 lightyear radius.\nThe story overall is nice though it could patch up some plot holes like \"Why not shoot the guy from the start of the the game before MC gets all attached and stuff?\", it could do that for once. However, that'd take away from the suspense that your father is a \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665, so?", "hours": 12.1, "username": "\u97ff", "products": 136, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 194, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-06", "text": "SPOILER ALERT!!!\n.\n.\n.\n.\n.\n.\n.\n.\n.\nIn my opinion, Assassin's Creed 3 is the best game of the series and Connor is the best assassin ever. Not because he has special skills or something, but he is the only one who makes mistakes (just like everyone) he fights for freedom (at first he wanted to save his village, but after killing his first target, he realised what being an assassin means), he sacrifised so much and he saw his mother burning alive and a lot of his close friends dying. Although his life was terrible and full of pain, he helps people without asking something in return. This is very inspiring for me. His life was the most poetic, close to me and realistic of all the assassins so far. Connor's sad story still makes me cry sometimes.\n(I am not going to apologize, I am sure my English were not so good...)", "hours": 159.3, "user_id": "76561198142151182", "username": "wayward-son", "products": 12, "early_access": false}
