{"product_id": "208480", "page": 203, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-05-04", "text": "Apart from the sea battles (which are fun), thought this was... meh...\nPlayed and loved AC1, 2 and brotherhood, but AC3 is a definite step backwards, and the whole thing feels decidedly rushed and unpolished.\nFirst off, the first 8 hours or so \"intro\" gameplay is dull. You spend most of it in cutscenes, or just wandering around with little to do (hey - let me spend half an hour assassinating rabbits!). Zero tension, and way too drawn out. The whole thing could have fitted easily into a 5 minute tutorial.\nThe whole release is also full of bugs. Multiple mission events don't trigger properly and require restarts, some missions appear on the map but cant be triggered at all. For some strange reason they've also changed the default key controls from the AC1&2 ones, so takes a while to get used to.\nFinally, a lot of the missions seem very prescriptive. Instead of AC1/2 style missions where your goals are generally very broad, AC3 missions (and not just the optional objectives required for full synchronization) are very specific (kill this person with a pistol from this location). Instead of the immersive experience you get from earlier titles, you end up just feeling like your task is to figure out which route the developers want you to take.", "hours": 15.2, "username": "rousseau", "products": 83, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 203, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-05-03", "text": "Boring story, Dull combat. Repetetive side missions. And a lot of small bugs. The only good thing are naval battles, but for that there's Black Flag.\nAC3 is not a bad game, but it's less interesting than it's predessessors. So if you haven't played AC before, better start with Ezio trilogy (AC2, Brotherhood, Revelations). And then skip AC3 and go to Black Flag.", "hours": 35.5, "username": "Snus", "products": 587, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 203, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-02", "text": "I don't like this game as much as the previous games, mainly because of the change in controls. There has been changes earlier, button changes and such, but in this game there are much less buttons to use at all. In previous games you feel more in control, one button for running, sprinting, jumping, climbing. In this game it is more or less just holding down one button and he will automatically run and jump from things where necessary/possible. It feels more like a movie you can steer sometimes but not as immersive as say, AC2. I never managed to finish this game, but I tried, I just didn't find it as fun as the other ones. Not a fan of American theme either which might add to it.\nBoat is fun though.", "hours": 10.8, "user_id": "76561198041869820", "username": "Vildvittra", "products": 79, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 204, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-02", "text": "This game brings the series up to the next level with a much improved seamless gameplay. The story is on par with Assassin's Creed II and the world is huge with lots to do.\nFor me I did not find Connor to be as likeable character as Ezio and had a hard time playing as him in the beginning but he does grow on you. It also felt like a huge tutorial almost half the game.\nThe game have some really nasty bugs and glitches which is annoying but nothing that will stop you from finishing the game.\nThe multiplayer is improved over the last games but it's still not balanced enough and I find myself playing mutliplayer only to get the Uplay award which is a boring chore.", "hours": 81.9, "username": "J.Jensen", "products": 756, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 204, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-05-01", "text": "The game is flawed. Stealth is bad, story is bad, the character is annoying. On top of that, he jumps on absolutely everything and it's almost impossible to complete some objectives.\nPros-you can captain a ship and learn about a lot of history....other than that, would not recommend.\nI'll play it through, but the mechanics are terrible.", "hours": 43.8, "user_id": "76561197974059746", "username": "amarrs103", "products": 124, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 204, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-04-30", "text": "Good game but kinda disappointing of the ending which connor was left alone with no one with his side. Moreover i don't have buy any weapon because all of them useless and only cause minor damage but craft weapon are pretty good. I love the naval missions in this series. Outfits are kinda lack in this game not much different variety in the shop but unlockables outfits looks great. Finally, there is not much stealth in this game but some point connor always engage on combat and some other point he become stealth assassin. The story of the game is good as native american who tries to protect his land and kinda fails at the end of the story.", "hours": 156.6, "user_id": "76561198163186494", "username": "Xce123", "products": 6, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 204, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-04-28", "text": "Here is my opinion of this dreaded game.\nI love AC franchise and I love playing however horrendous the games are. I even loved them once back in the time of brotherhood perhaps. For some reason Ubisoft packs their games with compatibility, control and graphics issues all the time; only for such expensive prices!\nIf you like the story and see what is the plot in the game (like I do) play it at your own expense. Otherwise, there are plenty of other \"fishes\" in the sea.", "hours": 37.4, "user_id": "76561197997464295", "username": "laxlaxor", "products": 110, "early_access": false}
