{"product_id": "208480", "page": 205, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-04-26", "text": "I love this game so much. Don't listen to all the haters who complain about it being bad, just because Connor is a bad character (and let's face it, he is). The new parkour system is incredible, everything feels connected, and while you still occasionally accidentally jump off buildings, this happens a lot less with the new engine. The combat is easy to get the hang of, and allows you to take out entire armies of enimies with ease, and taking a break from the war to hunt for some meat is always a fun distraction. I would say this was my second favourite Assassin's Creed, besides Assassin's Creed 4. You should buy it now, it really is a good game.", "hours": 127.8, "username": "Orkaherra", "products": 27, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 205, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-04-26", "text": "Assassin's Creed 3 gets a lot of hate, and I imagine a lot of it has to do with Connor, who is kind of a\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 after playing 3 games as Ezio who everybody loved. The gameplay in AC3 is pretty solid though, and when Connor is helping the homestead instead of killing redcoats, he's easier to like. The PC port doesn't run very well though. And I wish they could have made a few more tree models for the frontier viewpoints, got pretty old climbing the same tree 10 times.", "hours": 50.0, "username": "JasonTerminator", "products": 829, "early_access": false}
