{"product_id": "208480", "page": 210, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-04-06", "text": "A fun, buggy mess. Takes everything you loved from Assassin's Creed Revalations and expands upon it in this sequel. The story goes from pretty good to a little \"meh\" as you progress through Connor's story. But the story keeps you engaged enough to make your way through a ~20 hour story plus a ton of side mission content which can be entertaining too.\nThat being said, Connor as a character is a whiny mess. He'll often shift between hardcore assassin and angsty teenager which can be annoying. But the biggest issue with the game are the numerous bugs. I've had the game crash on multiple occasions. I've teleported seemingly randomly more than once. There are many visual bugs, such as NPCs materializing out of thin air OR magically changing outfit before your eyes. Pathing can be another problem where Connor will go out of his way to parkour off of walls repeatedly during a chase resulting in plenty of frustration. At one point the game locked me in some grey void causing me to have to close and re-open the game.\nGoing for $5 it is definitely worth the price, despite its many many flaws. I say play it for the gameplay and mechanics, which are both absolutely wonderful and will make up for the glaring problems.", "hours": 35.0, "username": "The Berenstain Bears", "products": 479, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 210, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-04-06", "text": "Jeez. I'm going through the whole series and... First Creed was nice, little boring but quite OK. II was quite nice along with all the expansions but III.... it's crap at best. It's boring. Controls are stupid (More than quite a few times I ended up jumping in front of enemies while I wanted to stay hidden, climbing trees is just ridiculous). Story is nice but the game is unplayable. I'm going to remove it at about 22% into the game (seems like it stopped progressing at about 20%) and maybe I'll be back when I'm bored with other titles. Also, in previous installments additional features were easy to do along the way (repairing shops, buying art etc) but in III? Stupid. Really hate this game.", "hours": 16.0, "username": "shyha", "products": 193, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 211, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-04-05", "text": "This is one of the best games I have ever played. This is the game where Ubisoft did almost everything right. Although the multiplayer doesn't work for me, the combat system was perfected, the mini map was there and the health bar was better. It left more room for customization with an entire homestead, and even after you finish the main story, there is always something to do. I believe that it is much better than Black Flag, especially in its hunting. The only thing that isn't better in this game than in Black Flag is the sailing. Other than that, the rest of the game is spectacular. 10/10", "hours": 48.8, "user_id": "76561198116237922", "username": "JustPotatoThings", "products": 116, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 211, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-04-05", "text": "Pros: Looks great, fairly emersive, cool story. The addition of firearms is a lot of fun!\nCons: Some game engine issues, slight bugs, this franchise is repetitive and expensive. Each game is pretty much the same.\nSeeing as I have played all the AC games up until and including this one, I doubt I will buy another from the franchise. They are all too similar for the price point.", "hours": 18.9, "user_id": "76561197977715797", "username": "Nazz", "products": 58, "early_access": false}
