{"product_id": "208480", "page": 213, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-03-28", "text": "I loved this game on the xbox and couldn't wait to play it when it went on sale for $4.99 USD, I was so excited to play this game with my new gaming rig that easily runs BF3 at Ultra in 1080p at an average of 155 fps. I wanted to see what fps i would get on this game... I have been getting around 20 fps AVERAGE. This game is far beyond broken as is any Assassin's Creed game for the PC. I gave up playing the game on my PC after logging around 20 hours. IF YOU HAVE ANY GRAPHICS CARD THAT IS NEWER THAN THE RECCOMENDED GRAPHICS CARD YOU WILL GET S****Y FPS.", "hours": 20.7, "username": "Art Vandelay", "products": 104, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 213, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-03-28", "text": "This is probably the weakest entry in the Assassin's Creed series. The setting is boring, there is less assassinations and the game is just a bit bland and generic. There is nothing which really stands out nor is there any mechanics or reasons to want to play it to the very end as the story isn't as interesting or contextual as the previous games in the series. Also, I really despise how the map works as it is confusing and poorly explained so I got lost frequently. Only purchase this if you are a die-hard Assassin's Creed fan. If you want the best game in the series then purchase Assassin's Creed 2. The only thing that is really well done in this one is the graphics which are pretty stellar.", "hours": 10.4, "username": "AyyySB", "products": 224, "early_access": false}
