{"product_id": "208480", "page": 217, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-20", "text": "Best bunch of Bucks i've spent in a while! The only downside was that the intro was really long and that you didn't really get to play as the assassin untill like 6 hours. Missions are really fun. I Really enjoy wandering around boston Killing red coats for the fun of it. 10/10 would buy again", "hours": 14.6, "user_id": "76561198113422067", "username": "Xpl0r3rr", "products": 82, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 217, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-03-20", "text": "Garbage, horrible story, \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 controls, voice acting equal to that of a high school kids first attempt at making movie. Combat is \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665, lead char is so out of place and does not even come close to fitting the role the game portrays him as.\nThen there is the usual garbage\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665port that Ubisoft is so famous for.\nThis game is more suited for downs syndrome patents as I'm sure most Ubicraps employes suffer from.\nSave your money and support devs that give a crap about there product.", "hours": 29.3, "username": "Lateralus", "products": 156, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 217, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-03-20", "text": "I personally think AC III is the worst game of the series I have played so far. It is not a bad game but compared to AC I and II it just lacks everything. The Story is actually quite interesting but also very confusing because the amount of different people that do not really play an important role is huge and every mission someone else gets introduced so the only deep character in the game is the assassin you play, everyone else is just some person that does something for or with you.\nThe town where a huge part of the game plays - Boston - doesnt have the character like the towns in AC II where you could spend hours and hours just exploring and doing anything. The architecture is rather boring (of course its related to the time AC III takes place but anyway.)\nBut as you see there are a lot of positive reviews so just try it out yourself maybe you like all that stuff that I didnt. But for me this was one of those games which I rather want to end quickly so I can play another game.", "hours": 12.4, "user_id": "76561198079664763", "username": "tr\u00edada oscura", "products": 131, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 217, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-20", "text": "A beautiful game with a beautiful atmosphere. Just wish taht you don't get a blackout in your area, it deletes your save.\nIt deleted mine.", "hours": 65.3, "username": "She's in a better place now", "products": 145, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 218, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-20", "text": "Fantastic game, very underrated. There are some systems and mechanics that are better fleshed out in AC4: Black Flag, but I really like the character of Conner. If you are a fan of the series you'll probably like this game, and make sure to grab the DLC, it is also quite good and explores an alternate reality where George Washington has gone mad with power!", "hours": 54.7, "user_id": "76561197991921123", "username": "meshuggah12345", "products": 3054, "early_access": false}
