{"product_id": "208480", "page": 218, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-19", "text": "A lot of people dislike this game for various reasons. It's true that the intro/tutorial to the game as Haytham Kenway and young Connor is long, and at times tedious, but for the most part it is well done, and was fairly enjoyable, if a little linear. Once that is done, the game becomes much more open and fun. The other criticism that most people give this game is Connor. I think he's really good. Sure, at first he is really awkward sometimes, and seems a little bit dead pan and lifeless, but he is an assassin after all, and on top of that has had some serious emotional trauma from his childhood. Later, once you begin to understand his character a little bit more, you start to despise those that he despises, and love the ones he loves, and you understand why he is doing what he is doing. All in all, I would say that this game really surprised me. I too, dear reader, read the negative reviews, and was skeptical to purchase this game. It was a choice I do not regret, and I really enjoyed the game.", "hours": 34.2, "username": "sad frog", "products": 80, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 218, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-19", "text": "Ok let me start with the cons\n1. story great as always\n2. Graphics a great bump from 2\n3. Introducing guns adds a new twist even though 2 had long range weapon too but still guns are cooler\nNow for the con, only one\nThe controls (I use a xbox 360 controller) feel really awkward, it's hard to explain, but I just can't feel the fast movement I felt when playing 2, I even tried playing 4 which is the sequel, it was was better, so that is a good thing FOR THE SEQUEL.\nOverall, a recommend for sure, but if you really want to experience the best of the series, assassin's creed 2 would be my choice.", "hours": 2.2, "username": "Zune", "products": 2220, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 218, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-03-19", "text": "Assassin's Creed III is not a game i enjoy playing other then a little Multi Player now and then, The story it outright terrible, it starts with this guy in 2012 who found some ancient mystical power to that was going to end the world and throughout the game your are playing in and out of the 1700's and the 2000's. In comparisan with Assassin's Creed Rogue this is bad.\nI would not recommend this game for anyone unless you enjoy extreme fantasy.", "hours": 1.5, "username": "Paul B\u00e4umer", "products": 54, "early_access": false}
