{"product_id": "208480", "page": 228, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-21", "text": "I choose \"Recommend\", as I have to pick something, but my feelings for this game are very mixed.\nPro:\n+ interesting, detailed plot with some unexpected plot twists\n+ visually stunning, huge open world\n+ well-prepared historical background\n+ a few new features: hunting, hiding, naval battles\nAgainst:\n- Connor is dull and flat\n- prologue part is way too long\n- bad texture quality on smaller objects (ex. doors and gravestones)\n- too little music\n- trade and strategic aspects have very unclear interface and, basically, could be completely omitted", "hours": 28.3, "username": "pdenton", "products": 103, "early_access": false}
