{"product_id": "208480", "page": 231, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-10", "text": "Assassin's Creed III is a good game, but it doesn't live up to what an Assassin's creed game should be. Sure it added a few new things like: updated graphics, actual hiding, and more user friendly menues. But the game lacked in some areas. The story took to long to get started and by the end I was more wanting to skip the cutscenes then watch them. It seemed like they were trying to make it really epic but ended up just plain over the top. The game is buggy (I lost count of how many times I got stuck in rocks).", "hours": 44.4, "username": "IceRicer", "products": 157, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 231, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-02-10", "text": "I apreciate the effort put into this game, but the result is not woth it.\nThe plot was never a strength of AC series, but in III its blandness showed the most. Not quite consistant Star Wars knock-off plot-wise, and most 'twists' made me raise my palm and lay it upon my forehead.\nThe second act was an improvement, Connor's relationship with his father, who is way more three-dimensional, seemed interesting enough.\nGameplay-wise: controls are as always clumsy and not changeable (that was a drag for me, cause holding RT and A at the same time is uncomfortable). Fights are boring, chases are not engaging, stealth is not rewarding.\nThe game's a mess. High-budget detailed product that is not worth spending time on.", "hours": 37.1, "username": "Scarface", "products": 392, "early_access": false}
