{"product_id": "208480", "page": 231, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-08", "text": "Ok first of all this is by far the best AC (from I to III). Combat is enhanced is more fluid and less static. Firearms no longer need long stupid aiming. And you get to drive a ship. Well on the other hand as I said this is the best AC so far it is also the worst AC when it comes to frustration. I became frustred so many times with this game... I mean glitches, bugs and other minor or major anoyances. Not to mention ridiculous pop-in and actually pop-out. Obviously there is no draw distance slider or setting and thus you're stuck with only one option even if you have beastly HW you can't do nothing about it. I was running away from guards in NY because I didn't want to fight them so I turned to side streets and 'pop' there was a whole dead squad shooting me.\nYou need to learn to live with it. Gameplay is solid, movement is quite better than in AC2, combat is much better than in AC2. And I almost forgot hunting, yes you can hunt animals and run through american wilderness.\n7/10", "hours": 32.0, "username": "RAMIEL", "products": 111, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 232, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-02-08", "text": "Well, here's the truth.\nThis game has a pretty good storyline, arguably the coolest protagonist, cool new features, and is set in a really ideal time period and location.\nBUT, you see that \"43.6 hrs on record\" up there? I'll tell you that maybe 10% of that is actual gameplay. The game lagged horribly, the game crashed right when you became Connor after an extremely long cutscene. Imagine trying to play a game and you have to play the boring beginning 8 times and watch the same 8 minute cutscene EIGHT TIMES. Then have the game be so laggy that it's basically unplayable, but fast enough that you think you can play it. Basically the gameplay was 10 times slower than it should have been resulting in 40 hrs of gameplay. This may work for you because I'm running AMD processor and graphics card.\nNow lets talk about how extremely ambitious this game was. Ubisoft basically thought they could make a game that should have been on a next gen. platform, but they through it on the old dogs. It's like trying to play Battlefield 4 on a Nintendo DS. Good luck.\nThis game is SOY GAY. I DONT EVEN WANNA TYPE ANYMORE BECAUSE IT MAKES ME SO ANGRY THAT THIS GAME WAS A TERRIBLE PORT FOR PC AND IT JUST SUCKED. I LOVE PEN15", "hours": 44.0, "username": "Hitler", "products": 92, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 232, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-02-08", "text": "AC2 trilogy was the best game story I ever played, graphics were nice, control was good everything was fine.\nAnd now I started playing AC3 and I just feal sad cause this game suck so bad. It has nothing for it. Lot of graphics bug, like thing not showing, thing disappear and a lot of collusion bug. Maybe with a better engine the game will be controlable but this Anvilnext engine is carbage. I'm not sure I will play another AC game, at least not with thie engine.\nI regret buying AC3-4 even if they were very cheap in steam sales.\nFor me, AC stop at Revelation, after that Ubisoft is just trying to make money and don't care about us, gamers.", "hours": 2.8, "username": "JFP", "products": 727, "early_access": false}
