{"product_id": "208480", "page": 239, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-01-13", "text": "Let me start off by saying.\nI liked this game. But the ending sucked weiner. The combat feels strong and made me feel like a god. All the characters are pretty interesting. But the backtracking, the chase sequences, and the last act of the game dropped my rating from an 8/10 to a 6/10. It feels like Ubisoft was going for something cool, but ran out of time and just shoved it out the door and rushed it. Only buy this game for the cool Tomahawk killing,naval fighting, and interesting characters. If none of those options interest you, just back the heck out. Also, the tutorial isn't half bad, Haythan is quite cool, and the beginning of the game is the strongest point in terms of story.", "hours": 17.9, "username": "jn tr po", "products": 87, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 239, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-01-13", "text": "The good:\n-Cool cutscenes.\n-you can climb  trees.\nThe Bad:\n-A still broken combat system.\n-A shoddy PC port with extremely awful optimization\n-A bland story that lacks personality\n-Extremely broken stealth mechanics.  Eavesdrop makes me pull my hair out.\n-Very cumbersome controls without a controller.", "hours": 6.1, "username": "shamalamalamalam", "products": 129, "found_funny": 4, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 239, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-12", "text": "While not the worst of the AC games I've played, it's not exactly the best.\nGameplay: 7.5/10. AC3 has simplified gameplay compared to the previous titles. It's actually not bad, since combat and freerunning have both been made a lot more fun by it. In regards of actual stealth, however, I found it lacking.\nGraphics and Art Style: 8/10. The previous AC games looked OK, but they were nothing special. This game has a major upgrade compared to them, and it ends up looking pretty nice.\nMusic and Sound Design: 7/10. Nothing stands out, although some scenes and gameplay sections were made a lot more exciting by the background music.\nWriting: 7/10. AC is no stranger to the cliffhanger, but this game has one of the cruelest and cheapest I've seen in a while. I won't take any more points away, though, because the first few hours carried one of the most unexpected and mind-explodingly logical twists I've ever experienced.\nStability and Glitch Control: 7/10. The game is still playable, and it's nowhere near as fukt as Unity (wa-hay, topical). But some were very immersion-breaking, and I remember very well one stealth level being royally messed up when rubberbanding caused an enemy corpse I had hidden to rocket right into view of the guards, leading to me being discovered. Similarly, I had to initiate a few restarts when I got stuck in world geometry.\nFinal score: 7.3/10. It's a good game, and I'm glad I played it, but I still recommend getting it on a sale.", "hours": 22.9, "username": "Troll Under The Bridge", "products": 350, "early_access": false}
