{"product_id": "208480", "page": 241, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-01-08", "text": "I could write about what's wrong with this game forever, but I won't, because nobody wants that not even me.\nHere's the deal, you play as Connor, an east coast Native American in colonial times whose home is destroyed by the Templar Order, which (you guessed it) sets you on a quest to joining the Assassin Brotherhood! Only after becoming the great Assassin you put literal hours of gameplay by this point into becoming, Connor turns into a whiney, brooding child who laments on how Assassin's and Templars can't simply work together to protect (read: control) the free world. After playing Assassin's Creeds 1, 2, Brotherhood, and Revelations, After building up the Assassin Brotherhood from the brink of destruction, Aftering fighting a shadow war through multiple games to reach this point you have absolutely nothing to show for it, \"Back to square one \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665, thanks for the cash!\" -Ubisoft. Oh, and Desmond dies at the end after touching a golden testicle or something. Who knows, the final cutscene only lasted about twelve seconds.", "hours": 13.4, "username": "Knight-Captain Hyperion", "products": 240, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
