{"product_id": "208480", "page": 241, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-08", "text": "Bought on sale for 5 or 7.50. Played 50 hours.\nA fun sandbox game, lots of diversions. Never got into crafting/trading much, so I might be missing out. I liked the ship mission mechanics - very pretty but very little tactics.\nCombat and freerunning are still very satisfying, though there's still the odd time where you jump out into space instead of that haystack, and the guards all feel like squishy paste or cheating \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665s. Tree running and hunting are fun new bits.\nIt tells a nice arching story. Incredibly heavy-handed all the time, but best taken as a parody of something.\nAlso, John de Lancie.", "hours": 50.7, "username": "Zerotan", "products": 565, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 241, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-08", "text": "80/100\nNice, different, but far AWAY from the Ezio Trilogy (AC 2)\nFor itself it\u00b4s a nice game with Assassination Theme during Civil War times in the United States.\nCombat style is more Bruiser/Tank.. lacks the stealthy part a lot.\nBut to even it out, you get a ship.. and you can equip it.. and become a Pirate Captain ^^\n--> AC:3 is good to kill some time in a nice setting with average Story! It fit\u00b4s between 2.5 Brotherhood and IV Black Flag.\n..just don\u00b4t expect AC:2 Ezio-Trilogy features or the better Overall Story and Combat from AC:4 Black Flag", "hours": 40.2, "user_id": "76561198075849015", "username": "wespe___o=/;;;:*", "products": 124, "early_access": false}
