{"product_id": "208480", "page": 248, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-29", "text": "Well, choosing whether I recommend this game or not was a difficult task. First of, I am a AC franchise fan, so I like the story a lot, and of course, this game, like all AC games is a must have. Still, compared to other games, it might have lost some of its story factor.\nWhat I did like:\nNavigating a 18 century ship. Nice experience.\nHunting. No, I'd really NEVER hunt in real live, but the hunting in this game, due to its economics, is strangely rewarding.\nWhat I did not like:\nIt's basically the same, isn't it?\nDesmond's Father\nAt first, due to the possibility to travel between maps, the game is a bit confusing.\nThis a very superficial short review, so I will just keep it like this (short).\nBuy this game when it's on a deal price.", "hours": 195.2, "username": "Mikylin.BO.BGZ", "products": 1355, "early_access": false}
