{"product_id": "208480", "page": 259, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-12-13", "text": "8 hours in and here's what I've done so far -\nWalked around Boston\nRun around Boston\nClimbed around Boston\nRode a horse arond Boston\nPlayed checkers in a sailboat\nWandered the sewers for an hour\nPet a sheep\nGone on a few missions that involve mostly walking and/or running around Boston at choppy framerates\nThe platforming is idiot proof and requires ZERO thought.  The cutscenes are mind-numbing.  The combat is sketchy and far and few between.  \"Stalking\" basically means \"walking around quietly\".  How fun is that in a video game!\nI'm going back to playing Splinter Cell.", "hours": 24.0, "user_id": "76561198024759190", "username": "Erlich Bachman", "products": 113, "early_access": false}
