{"product_id": "208480", "page": 259, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-12", "text": "As a long time fan of the series ever since first playing as Altair, I had high hopes for AC III. Having just finished Ezio's amazing story that spanned three games (as well as a bit more info about Altair from Revelations), I felt the series hit a high note. AC III, however, seems to be the beginning of a decline. Everything about the game exuded grand scope, pure awesome - it just didn't hit those notes. The ending was a bit of a shocker too. Everything about the game just seemed to meet its potential halfway. However, the naval combat mechanics and the 'tree roam' were interestingly done.\nAll in all, I would recommend this game as it is indeed a valuable sector of the story arc of the original 'Minerva' series.\n7/10", "hours": 11.7, "user_id": "76561198166563648", "username": "satan=santa", "products": 23, "early_access": false}
