{"product_id": "208480", "page": 261, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-12-06", "text": "I have spent enough of my life on this game so this review will be brief:\n1) Loads of promise that kept me hooked. However, the promised never developed. Instead there was...\n2) An utter lack of focus and unnecessary gimmicks. In short, a sprawling morass which, I suspect, led to,...\n3) A ridiculous amount of bugs, for any game, let alone one so long past release.\n4) In addition, Connor is a completely obnoxious protagonist and quite possibly the worst assassin ever. He is set in...\n5) A contrived, unnecessarily wordy, and annoyingly forced story.\nIn summary, get Assassin's Creed Brotherhood, Revelations, or possibly Black Flag.", "hours": 46.1, "username": "Adam T", "products": 204, "early_access": false}
