{"product_id": "208480", "page": 262, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-12-05", "text": "AC3 is a long game, composed of a series of detached, meandering plot points and stocked with flat, unlikable characters. Classic AC gameplay (freerunning / open world / combat) is crowded out by minigames that range from the boring to the aggravating and many of the freerunning missions are essentially on rails, reducing the whole thing to a series of quicktime events. Collectables abound, but the payoff is slim and the majority of them only exist to feed an utterly pointless economy-based grinding system.\nEven at under $10 I felt robbed. This one is for completists only - catch up on the story on wikipedia or something and save yourself the trouble.", "hours": 51.2, "username": "chrk", "products": 140, "early_access": false}
