{"product_id": "208480", "page": 279, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-11-01", "text": "Decent entry into the franchise, but not as good as AC 2 due to the mostly linear story missions. Great atmosphere though, the American Civil War is an interesting background for an AC game. Took me around 165 hours to 100% complete, so there's a lot of content and collectibles here to enjoy, including some mini games that get old after a while. You also get to ruthlessly murder around 3/4 of the redcoat population.\nOverall, a solid game.", "hours": 169.5, "username": "Macheti", "products": 644, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 279, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-11-01", "text": "Finished this game in 67 hours on the count.\nI think it is a good game in terms of combat mechanics, new features such as controlling a ship. Fun idea with homestead instead of just workshop.\nThe bad things - sometimes the combat gets a little messy, mainly due to main character trying to climb an object instead of just running. I still haven't found a sensible way of combating brutes - imagine one of those guys can stop your combo and smash you in your teeth with his head for damage similar to officers sabre.\nSome people complain about the health regeneration, but I actually love that feature. The combat system is simply so much fun, that in many cases I'd rather jump into the fray and do some slashing.\nPlot - this is my personal opinion, so take it or leave it. The Main protagonist (connor) is a complete retard. Literally, in a \"how stupid and naive one can be\" from 0 to 10,  he scores a \"bag of rocks\" score. Naive as a child, stubborn as a mule and often plain foolish. In many cases I felt \"by all the Hells, why are we going to do this?! This makes no sense!\" And in the end proceeding with another display of idiocy in a cut scene. I will refrain from spoiling here, but seriously - I don't think there ever was a more stupid \"assassin\"", "hours": 67.5, "user_id": "76561198153956434", "username": "Nevasith", "products": 141, "early_access": false}
