{"product_id": "208480", "page": 282, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-10-26", "text": "This game has been hard for me to complete, not because of difficulty, but because it feels alien when compared to the cadre of AC2 games.  It is similar to the differences between AC1 and AC2, but in a worse direction, not a better direction.  I have heard excellent reports on AC4, so I will hold out hope.  I may finish it someday.", "hours": 477.7, "user_id": "76561197982416990", "username": "apocalyptic_socks", "products": 50, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 282, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-26", "text": "A solid entry in the Assassin's Creed franchise set during America's war for independence which is brilliantly portrayed by its many iconic historical figures and authentic-looking 18th-century New York and Boston and battles - Assassin's Creed once again doesn't disappoint in that regard.\nI also enjoyed the concept of a Native American main character as there are very few main characters in games that aren't caucasian, sadly, and this is intially a great thing until you realise how unlikable Ratonhnhkat\u00e9:ton/Connor is -  Ezio Auditore he is not. He's always brooding, sporting a melancholic attitude and the passion for those around him that you felt when playing as Ezio is non-existent. But if you can get around that you'll delight in the new parkour system through the trees and mountainous areas of the game which is a refreshing change of pace and terrain from the long-standing series.\nAdded to that are the glorious naval ship battles on the high seas which are incredibly fun and tactical as shots need to be timed in order to hit the vessel you're targeting and not get wasted in a rising wave for example. Navigating in concert with the direction of the wind is also important and makes for a joyous and riveting series of battles on the high seas :D\nThe game also concludes Desmond's story and while it's great that he finally begins to shine physically as an assassin, he's as whiney as always and his ending is seriously anti-climactic and a head-scratcher.\n8/10", "hours": 59.9, "username": "Valassi", "products": 211, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 282, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-10-25", "text": "A very bad Assassin's Creed game. This game is nearly unplayable due to bad camera angles and trees blocking your view. the horse riding makes missions almost unbeatable as the horses will not get within 3 feet of a rock, stump nor tree, and comes to a dead stop if near any impedament. Requires U-Play launcher. Desmond missions dont really advance the plot in any maningful way. as a fan of fun i can not rec this game to anyone, even the setting is boring.", "hours": 36.4, "user_id": "76561198006700052", "username": "CarAxadent", "products": 102, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 282, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-25", "text": "What can I say: it's Assassin's Creed..!\nIt is a precious sequel of the story. I wished it wasn't lived in near history of US. Because I like the historic themed games that pass in really old times like the first Assassin's Creed game. But this one is a very successful game of fabolous graphics and gameplay...", "hours": 15.3, "user_id": "76561198088249884", "username": "conquerro", "products": 239, "early_access": false}
