{"product_id": "208480", "page": 284, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-19", "text": "I love it.\nIt's a nice piece of progression of the series.\nThe hunting aspect and Homestead is alot of fun, the naval warfare is great, and the story compelling.\nThe gunplay is a little fiddly and slow, but so was power and lead balls.\nThe hand to hand combat is enjoyable though a little too easy sometimes but the combos when hit are certainly interesting and great to watch.\nThe graphics are great and not too taxxing on systems for the quality and the enviroment is large an varied.\nOccationally I find myself losing immersion with the game at certain points but they aren't deal breakers.\nI'd recommend it to anyone", "hours": 17.3, "user_id": "76561197993632034", "username": "Glendinho", "products": 297, "early_access": false}
