{"product_id": "208480", "page": 286, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-10-17", "text": "There's something off about this Assassin's Creed...\nConnor doesn't feel like a strong character, the gameplay isn't quite as fun as its predecessor, and even though I'm a fan of the time period, the American Revolution was a\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665setting to put the game in.\nThe game just drags on and on... and you never really seem to get anything done or do anything exciting for long periods of time.\nThe best thing to come out of this game was the ship fighting mechanic, which was heavily focused on in AC4, which I think is a much much much superior game.\nSkip this game if you don't really care about the whole \"Desmond\" story anyway. It'll be worth your time and money to do so.", "hours": 21.6, "username": "PhoenixRR", "products": 214, "early_access": false}
