{"product_id": "208480", "page": 294, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-08", "text": "I have heard some people say they had trouble with UPlay or just general crashes. Nope. I got uplay up and running fine within 5 minutes. The gameplay is stunning. I stood in awe at the framerate. I believed it would run improperly but it ran fine. Parkour mechanics that are beyond mindblowing. And lets not forget the jaw dropping combat. 10/10. And i don't throw around 10/10s lightly. If you're reading reviews before getting it i definitely recomend it.", "hours": 108.3, "username": "A Notably Superior Pringle", "products": 96, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 294, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-08", "text": "This game is good, not gonna blow your mind (the story is really dumb, and conner is no assassin) but good.\nDETAIL:\nThis game has a massive mix of diffrent parts, strung together in a impressive way. From the story missions, which are interesting but confusing (see further down), to the homested missions trading and recruting assassins (PLEASE BRING THIS BACK UBISOFT). Note the game is not 100% cohesive game many of the side missions are detatched and weird, but it is still 75%, better then most games.\nThe stroy is the games weak spot, it can be summerized into 3 words - \"Where's charls lee\". At one point they are face to face and he does nothing, becuase game length. As such conner is really 1-D (not really, but for about 60% of the time), however haythem (the main villain) is very deep and has really good caracter.\nThis game has alot of fun to offer, but it is not a real AC game, take that into account.", "hours": 143.9, "user_id": "76561198089550980", "username": "GGame.exe", "products": 45, "early_access": false}
