{"product_id": "208480", "page": 295, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-07", "text": "Great game.. Stil i bought the deluxe edition.\nWith the season pass key.. (this unlocks everything right?\nStill no idea why you get the benedict arnold DLC Key, its to no use if you have the season pass wich you also get if you buy the deluxe edition of Assassin creed III\nNice game good graphics", "hours": 4.7, "user_id": "76561198011414784", "username": "GNR-W91-NL", "products": 28, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 295, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-07", "text": "I was really looking forward to Assassin's Creed III in mid 2012. The game looked like a more refined version of the second game which I loved. Unfortunately, what was delivered was a glitchy, unfocused, and horribly paced game. I still reccomend it, but if you are in it for the epic battles and story, you may be dissapointed. Also the Music is phenomenal, the theme rivals \"Ezio's Family (Main Theme)\" from Assassin's Creed II.\nOverall 6/10\nDLC 6.5/10\n+Naval Missions\n+Good PC Port\n+DLC Grants Fun Abilities and Interesting Concept\n-Weak Story and Pacing\n-Lack of Steath\n-Texture and Objects Glitch Constantly\n-Tailing Missions\nI reccomend just spending your money on Assassins's Creed IV: Black Flag", "hours": 64.7, "username": "Hontros", "products": 290, "early_access": false}
