{"product_id": "208480", "page": 300, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-09-19", "text": "This game is adequate, but as a triple A submission that likely had many millions of dollars put into development, it falls quite short. I didn't connect with the stroy in any way, bugs had a way of finding me rather than the other way around, and most of the missions boil down to running from point a to point b and stabbing a guy with little to do in between. The one good thing I'll say about this game is that it's a pretty great time to just walk around town with the law enforcement\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665at you, so that you may take down all comers with your bare hands. Yet at that rate I may as well have just played either of the Arkham Batman games.", "hours": 23.0, "user_id": "76561198042767131", "username": "Whiskers", "products": 313, "early_access": false}
