{"product_id": "208480", "page": 308, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-08-14", "text": "Another great game from Assassin's Creed series. I really like playing as Haytham Kenway the templar just a bit more than Connor, but taking part in battles was quite intriguing ... especially naval battles. It was a great conclusion for Desmond; although, i would prefer to be given a choice rather than at the end side with Juno. I am looking forward to AC4.", "hours": 27.0, "username": "Maciej Medyk", "products": 333, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 308, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-08-14", "text": "I really wanted this game to be good, and I tried my hardest to keep going, but this is total\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 The PC port is a complete disaster. Bugs everywhere; lips out of sync, horrible physics, items just disapear in to thin air. I'd say this game is a prime example on why you don't set unrealistic timelines on your developement team just to get the game out so you can make profits at expense of the gamer's satisfaction.\nGameplay is fun.\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 it's actually extremely fun... but that's when you actually get a chance to play. Missions last less than 15 minutes, and you're then switched back to watching cut scenes. I wouldn't be surprised if after recording some of this, I would see less than 50% of the game actually being controlled by the player. It's a game, not a f***ing movie.\nGreat work Ubisoft, you went ahead and killed an amazing series. I highly doubt I'll be purchasing any other AC games from you in the future.", "hours": 3.8, "username": "InvisiblexRed", "products": 213, "early_access": false}
