{"product_id": "208480", "page": 327, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-30", "text": "Assasin's Creed 3 \u0e40\u0e1b\u0e47\u0e19\u0e40\u0e01\u0e21\u0e17\u0e35\u0e48\u0e19\u0e48\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e19\u0e43\u0e08\u0e15\u0e31\u0e48\u0e07\u0e41\u0e15\u0e48\u0e20\u0e32\u0e04 1-3 \u0e1c\u0e21\u0e40\u0e25\u0e48\u0e19\u0e21\u0e32\u0e17\u0e38\u0e01\u0e20\u0e32\u0e04\u0e41\u0e25\u0e49\u0e27 \u0e22\u0e01\u0e40\u0e27\u0e49\u0e19 \u0e20\u0e32\u0e04 4 \u0e41\u0e25\u0e30\u0e40\u0e01\u0e21\u0e19\u0e35\u0e49\u0e19\u0e35\u0e49\u0e40\u0e1b\u0e47\u0e19\u0e40\u0e01\u0e21\u0e17\u0e35\u0e48\u0e2a\u0e19\u0e38\u0e01\u0e21\u0e32\u0e01\u0e25\u0e2d\u0e01\u0e0b\u0e37\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e21\u0e32\u0e40\u0e25\u0e48\u0e19\u0e14\u0e39\u0e41\u0e25\u0e49\u0e27\u0e08\u0e30\u0e23\u0e39\u0e49\u0e27\u0e48\u0e32\u0e21\u0e31\u0e19\u0e40\u0e1b\u0e47\u0e19\u0e22\u0e31\u0e07\u0e44\u0e07", "hours": 56.5, "user_id": "76561198127507046", "username": "Happy", "products": 34, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 327, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-06-30", "text": "What I consider to be the low point of the Assassins creed series. Unlikable characters (Connor is always angry while maybe reasonable due to his past makes him unlikable especially in the way he treats his friends.) a new setting that doesn\u2019t play to the strengths of the series (the cities of America are just being constructed and are small decreasing the height you can climb from past games) and even 2 years later it is littered with bugs.", "hours": 54.1, "username": "Vanger", "products": 376, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 328, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-06-30", "text": "Nice graphics, but that's about it. Personally, this was the game that ruined AC for me, utterly boring when most of your time is spent traveling from location to location which should have be saved by 'map traveling'. The story drags on and on and didn't interest me in the slightest. After playing half of it (couldn't commit anymore than that) I realised there were no big assassinations that there were in the previous 3 games, which for me was the most fun part of AC: setting up a perfect assassination by being undetected. But the closest Assassin's Creed III gets to this is trying to remain undetected whilst evesdropping 2 guards.", "hours": 12.7, "user_id": "76561197995221207", "username": "cmd_", "products": 103, "early_access": false}
