{"product_id": "208480", "page": 329, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-29", "text": "The next part in the story of Desmond Miles. Interesting setting in the nature with the native americans. Awesome missions and historical settings is great. Though, from the Assassin's Creed franchise, I think this is the least epic one. However, it is still a very good game like you are used to with the previous titles. Definitely worth buying (especially during sales)", "hours": 41.3, "username": "RMNiels", "products": 90, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 329, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-06-28", "text": "Probably the weakest entry in the series, behind even Revelations--which is saying something. Not particularly fun, and full of useless, boring side content. Poor writing and uncompelling present-day sections tie the poop pile together.", "hours": 23.3, "username": "Black Magic", "products": 294, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 329, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-28", "text": "This was my first Assassin's Creed game and I absolutely loved it. Would definitely reccomend it to anyone.", "hours": 9.7, "user_id": "76561198037965167", "username": "Autoshotsbrb", "products": 232, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 329, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-06-28", "text": "I may be done with Assassin's Creed III. 12 hours in, still in the \"tutorial\" and now it's turning into a  colonial homestead simulator.  Ubisoft, if I had wanted that I would have bought Banished (I didn't want that)!\n\nI think I've been an \"assassin\" for 15-20 minutes so far in this game & gopher running back and forth doing stupid & boring tasks for people the rest of that time.\nI keep thinking: \"This has got to really get going soon!\" but then they decide to introduce a whole new batch of stuff I couldn't care less about.\nIn the last \"mission\" I completed I got to send some wood I bought through a menu option to a merchant via another menu option.  I was shaking with excitement!\nThe next mission I'm supposed to attend to entails going to buy a few cannons & hire some guys for my boat... really!?! FUN!\n\nI played (some) of AC1 (got bored), all of 2a, 2b & 2c (burnt out on these and took a long break before this one).  It would have been really nice if they would have added \"animus tutorials\" accessible from a menu for newcomers so that veteran players didn't have to play through all the initial hand-holding of both the old & newer mechanics.  Pop-up some tooltips while I'm playing if you want, but dang guys, just let me start the game when I START THE GAME.\nI'll update this if I keep going and change my mind, but it shouldn't take this long to get to \"the good\" part in any game.", "hours": 11.3, "username": "AZAG0TH", "products": 1498, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 329, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-28", "text": "the game is really fun", "hours": 54.4, "user_id": "76561198072448396", "username": "aerrownine", "products": 82, "early_access": false}
