{"product_id": "208480", "page": 332, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-06-26", "text": "Buggy as all get out and kind of boring. I like the setting at least", "hours": 13.8, "username": "ShiftySatchmo", "products": 460, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 332, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-06-26", "text": "Once the novelty of the new engine, new setting and graphical upgrade from the previous games wore off, I found this game disappointing. The world is so much emptier than Rome and Constantinople. The pacing is atrocious with new mechanics still being introduced half-way through the game, around the time Conner gets his robes and his objective. The story was really tedious and kind of pretentious as well. Conner especially emulates those traits, and I didn't feel as cool playing as him like I did with Ezio.", "hours": 10.6, "username": "Good Drink", "products": 183, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 332, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-26", "text": "Beautiful environments.\nDepressing story about revenge.\nSome really tedious elements.\nDesmond's story isn't satisfying.\nThe game can be really enjoyable, many story elements and graphics are really wonderful.", "hours": 38.4, "username": "Flame", "products": 457, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 332, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-26", "text": "It's a fun game with good graphics, almost no glitches, and good gameplay mechanics.\nIt story department lacks a lot because the main character is just not that interesting. The game makers do a good job of showing the templars not in a totally bad way but it's just glanced over for feather collecting (seriously). There are a lot of things which are basically useless (?) like trapping, hunting, and upgrades for your farm because all they give you is money and you honestly dont need that many upgrades to beat the game so its a lot of wasted time which you can do but is not necessary. The Desmond sections are pretty fun but the story is basically running at full speed by the end and a lot of the backstory with Juno is.... weird.\nOverall, not the best Assassin's Creed game but fun for what it is.", "hours": 41.5, "user_id": "76561198108183039", "username": "DiabolicalDude", "products": 412, "early_access": false}
