{"product_id": "208480", "page": 333, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-25", "text": "Although the story line isnt the best and the protagonist Connor isn't remarkably interesting. The mechanics and general play of the game is enough to keep you hooked for hours!", "hours": 153.6, "user_id": "76561198039527255", "username": "TStan", "products": 263, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 333, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-25", "text": "Certainly not a bad game -- I recommend it. However, I have a hard time having Connor be the successor to Ezio. The game plays very smoothly, looks great, and continues the epic story that the Assassin's Creed series has built up. A game of this caliber during a steam sale - certainly can't go wrong!", "hours": 58.1, "username": "Charlie Clutch", "products": 136, "early_access": false}
