{"product_id": "208480", "page": 333, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-25", "text": "While i found the main character Connor to be a very boring and bland character the game itself was fun to play. Experiencing AC gameplay within an American Revolution setting was pretty exciting and the world is large and interesting.\nThere are quite a few annoying movement and climbing bugs that get annoying.\nOverall the story and setting was worth it for me to play it once, but i hope they seriously never revisit Connor's story; he's a very boring protagonist.", "hours": 55.9, "username": "JappersMcJappers", "products": 133, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 333, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-25", "text": "I think that is defintely my favorite Assassins Creed game of the series. It introduced free running that seemed that logical from the start. Being able to parkour through trees just brought a reinvigorating organic feel to the series. As may will say because of this and the choice of area in the world, it leaves some areas with nothing to jump onto. This is true and a drawback, but does not take away (in my mind) how wonderful of a game this is. The plot line is soild and advances the story line (the flaw in revelations and brotherhood) and is set in the american revolution that although is not fair of a comment but is indeed one of my all time favorite time periods. Worth it, especially now that it is down in price", "hours": 63.7, "user_id": "76561198095173295", "username": "taken", "products": 158, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 333, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-25", "text": "It is the best game of all the ac exept ac black flag. I play it in low settings and it has VERY GOOD GRAPHICS , the story is awesome, the technics of killing or doing parkour. It is just awesome. You can drive a ship you can do anything you want and you can explore a BIG WORLD. Guys trust me, you gonna love this game!!!!!!", "hours": 10.7, "user_id": "76561198099625383", "username": "The_Godfather_(\u039d\u03bf\u03bd\u03cc\u03c2)", "products": 41, "early_access": false}
