{"product_id": "208480", "page": 340, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-15", "text": "Once you've killed every 'cop' in every city about 10 times, the game gets boring. Also, Uplay is absolute\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 I can't play any of my Uplay games without an internet connection. It's sounds like a minor thing, but I have data caps and once they decide to limit my internet, I get speeds of 25 kb/s and  nothing works. Seriously, take a lesson from Rockstar's Social Club. When you start up GTA IV, for example, you just enter your account info and you're good to go, even without internet. I payed about $100 into Assassin's Creed 3 and Far Cry 3, and it looks like it's $100 absolutley wasted because of \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 DRM. They also switched back to the old Captcha system on the website, you know the one. You get one set of numbers, but need to fill out two Captcha boxes. I think Ubisoft forgot Computer Science 3.", "hours": 78.5, "username": "HunterSThompson", "products": 74, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 340, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-14", "text": "Looking at how many bugs were patched I can see why it wasn't well received upon released. However I got it on sale for $12 and had a blast with it. Graphically it's very impressive, especially during the in-game winter season and the combat is superb. More complex than previous Assassin's Creed games with enemy variety requiring you to use specific methods for defeating them.\nThat said the story falls apart abysmally at the end of the game. No doubt to apparent cuts late in development.\nStill, if you can get it on sale, it's a pretty fun time.", "hours": 74.8, "username": "doctor 7", "products": 1113, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 340, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-14", "text": "Poorly-written code everywhere; the missions are buggy, the AI that is used to, for example, hide in hay piles does not work (most of the time, your character jumps right back out); Boston is a horribly un-optimized piece of garbage.\nAvoid this game. It is awful.\nUpdate: after a significant video card update, this game performs much better. It's still poorly optimized for PC, but, if your rig is powerful enough in all respects, this old game works well enough. The \"Tyranny of King Washington\" DLC is where this game shines best, honestly, as far as gameplay goes, if at least just for the fact that fast-travel to mission points was implemented in this (in the base game, you have to spend the time needed to run to each mission point, outside of inter-location travel).", "hours": 38.7, "username": "Crispy Tacos", "products": 726, "early_access": false}
