{"product_id": "208480", "page": 346, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-05-15", "text": "6/10\nthis is the second worst AC after AC Liberation HD\nthe story is good enough, but it will be much better if Ubisoft could execute it more seriously, in aspect of gameplay, it's \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665, the enemy AI, the notoriety system, the stealth, etc it's really unpolished.\nthe enemies can sometimes too magical to spot you behind the wall, but sometimes too stupid to realize that you're hiding in the bushes, it really needs more small improvement, the climbing is really unrealistic and climbing a tall building to do synchronization is really unchallenging...\nif only there's no annual release system, Ubisoft could make a far better AC3, if only...", "hours": 47.1, "username": "nyctophiliacfox", "products": 53, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 346, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-14", "text": "A Vast improvement over the other games in the series. While continuing the excellent story line.\nThis game is full of amazing detail in every aspect; Story, Graphics, ambiance, environment, sound and more.\nI would recommend this for the mere fact that it is always fun to play, and there's just so much to do in it.\nJust finished \"The Tyranny of Washington\" DLC, and it's a must play if you enjoyed AC3. It also seems to set up AC4 in a minor way, but excellent story driven DLC however.", "hours": 29.3, "username": "Doomtack", "products": 1640, "early_access": false}
