{"product_id": "208480", "page": 359, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-25", "text": "It's better than the critics gave it credit for, but there's a pretty big asterisk.  It doesn't really take off until a good 6 hours in, and the movement just doesn't feel as good as in previous titles - something I primarily attribute to the architectural style of the period,  which was somewhat unavoidable.  Play it if you need closure on Desmond's trilogy, but be prepared for a painfully long intro.  Everything else is similar enough to previous titles as to hardly warrant a mention, though the addition of naval combat is a fantastic new direction, and foreshadows AC4.", "hours": 123.0, "username": "Pirateguybrush", "products": 618, "early_access": false}
