{"product_id": "208480", "page": 359, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-23", "text": "The story about an assassin during the british colonies war of independece is quite interesting and can not be found often in games like Zombies, World War II or Medevil based games. The game itself is pretty amazing. A huge world to explore, many sidequests, an easy to learn combat system and a crafting system that gives you the cherry you are looking for on the whipped cream of your ice cream.", "hours": 0.6, "username": "Purim", "products": 235, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 359, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-03-22", "text": "yep, this stinks. I have steam to play a game. you charge me and then you require me to log on to UPLAY?  what the heck?\nThis is my last time buying on your stupid site. this is why people play xbox or hard drive PC games. cloud games aren't really ours are they?  you guys wish to make yourselves look smart with your juvenile tactics.", "hours": 15.7, "user_id": "76561198085704318", "username": "MooGoesCow99", "products": 82, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 360, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-22", "text": "The PC version of Assassin's Creed III definitely has it's problems. It is buggy and unoptimised, and even worse is the forced inclusion of Uplay.\nHowever the game itself is pretty enjoyable. The sea sections are the best part and you can see why Ubisoft focused on them more in the sequel, Black Flag. The era is well realised and can be quite immersive, and the new tree running abilities feel so core to the gameplay that it's a wonder we didn't have them in previous entries. The combat is fairly easy, press X to stab redcoats, but the music is good, which really adds to the setting. It works well as historical tourism. Also, the side missions are pretty essential if you want a full experience, as there is a major spoiler at the end of one of them.\nThough worth noting is the protagonist, Connor, has less personality than a potato.", "hours": 51.3, "username": "Bointon", "products": 654, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 360, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-03-22", "text": "Game-breaking glitches that cause you to constantly reload a checkpoint, terrible voice acting (except for Haytham), and controls that have somehow taken several massive steps back since ACII. I remember when Ezio could, for the most part, do the things you actually wanted him to. In ACIII, you'll be lucky if you don't accidentally climb up the same tree half a dozen times while in the middle of another scripted foot chase.\nDo yourself a favour and avoid it, the story's not even worth the trouble.", "hours": 63.2, "username": "Captain Mazda", "products": 153, "early_access": false}
