{"product_id": "208480", "page": 362, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-03-10", "text": "Save your money and don't buy this game.  The controls are unbelievably cumbersome and the storyline is a flop.  Missions are terse and lacking action.  This feels more like wasted time walking from cutscene to cutscene in a terrible B-list movie.  Regardless, you'll spend more time watching your character climb every possible piece of the environment... except what you're actually trying to climb.  This is the worst $20 I've spent in years.  Don't make the same mistake.", "hours": 26.8, "user_id": "76561197961011030", "username": "I'm a computer", "products": 40, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 362, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-10", "text": "This game overall is a ok game you can say.    It has its moments,but can feel dull.     For example you can be raiding a fort,then be bored going somewhere on horse.     Don't get me wrong it has its good parts,but compared to the hype and excitement it had,don't expect a jaw-dropping must have game.\nThe verdict,its a \"ok\" game and honestly don't feel like your missing out on anything.", "hours": 35.8, "username": "SirToasty", "products": 42, "early_access": false}
