{"product_id": "208480", "page": 374, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-21", "text": "How the \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 did this game make it out of beta testing? The potential is there for a great game, and maybe playing AC4 before AC3 spoiled me; but for \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665s sake launching the game is an ordeal as it frequently locks up at the main loading screen.\nIf you manage to get past the main menu (which is a herculean feat to be sure) you are then treated to\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665poor tutorials that do more to confuse than inform and terribly placed checkpoints that can have you running through the same 15 minute sequence just because you failed to abide by 1 easily failable objective.\nSpare yourself the rage; give this game a pass, the sequel to this game has all the fun and none of the grief, if you want to explore the plot of this \"game\" read the wiki page; but don't blow your money on this trash heap", "hours": 73.5, "username": "Strelok", "products": 177, "early_access": false}
