{"product_id": "208480", "page": 379, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-07", "text": "I was appealed by the theme and the beautiful graphics. While they're still absolutely stunning and gorgeous, I decided to stop playing this game.\nUtterly disappointing.\n- Very convoluted controls. It's really like playing a console game. One button does many things, convoluted menus, uncontrolled movements, very unnuanced.\n- Complete lack of freedom. The game is extremely linear with no customization for your character, let alone the path you're taking.\n- Very slow plodding along of the storyline. It bores you to death.\n- Combat goes from ridiculously easy (hacking away 20 enemies without breaking a sweat) to inexplicably difficult with four enemies beating the living daylights out of you without you even knowing what happened.\nExtremely not recommended.", "hours": 30.4, "user_id": "76561198048806414", "username": "Calriel", "products": 116, "early_access": false}
