{"product_id": "208480", "page": 388, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-12", "text": "Once again, an absolute TOP-game by Ubisoft:\n- Hammer Graphik\n- Interesting, varied and exciting story that never ends\n- Total loss of reality (because of animus, this, that, pineapple)\n- Extensive and indescribable movement and combat system (trees as a means of transportation, weapons diversity)\n- An enormous number of individual NPC's (realistic animals, detailed characters and more animals!)\nAll in all one of the best games of the series and in general one of the best games ever. Prerequisite: Powerful PC. And the best there is already a sequel and it will likely be several more to follow!\nMal wieder ein absolutes TOP-Game von Ubisoft:\n- Hammerm\u00e4\u00dfige Grafik\n- interesante, abwechsulungsreiche und spannende Story die niemals aufh\u00f6rt\n- totalen Realit\u00e4tsverlust (wegen Animus, dies, das, Ananas)\n- umfangreiches und unbeschreibliches Bewegungs- und Kampfsystem (B\u00e4ume als Fortbewegungsmittel, Waffenvielfalt)\n- enorm viele und individuelle NPC's (realistische Tiere, detailierte Charaktere und nochmehr Tiere!!! )\nAlles in allem eines der besten Spiele der Reihe und auch im allgemeinen eines der Besten Spiele \u00fcberhaupt. Voraussetzung: Leistungsstarker PC. Und das beste es gibt schon jetzt ein Fortsetzung und es werden wahrscheinlich noch mehrere folgen!!!", "hours": 73.5, "user_id": "76561198101505954", "username": "FUCKER", "products": 31, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 388, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-12", "text": "Despite the change of the combat system in Assassin's Creed 3, the game overall was a brilliant hit for me. Assassins was really the thing for me. When I played, I experienced. I felt like part of the Assassin Order and I'm pretty sure every other player who played AC up to 3 have felt that way. The storyline and locations was amazing, breathtaking and mesmerizing. As you play as a Native American doing his best to protect his people, you will engulf in his revolution and culture. Truly another great title from Ubisoft. 9.8 / 10 :D", "hours": 39.3, "username": "Cydrox", "products": 200, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 388, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-11", "text": "Assassins Creed 3 is one of the better games in the series.  The combat is fun and has been greatly improved since the last game in the series, the free running is also greatly improved bow you can free run in trees.\nThe only thing i found dissapointing was the money you earn, you can get the best stuff early on and i found myself with piles of cash at the end of the game with nothing to spend it on.", "hours": 23.9, "username": "danieltownsend21", "products": 14, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 388, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-11", "text": "Pros: Good Story, Much better writing than Brotherhood and Revolations.  Much better combat then a lot of the games in the series. Great Ship to Ship sea battles and nearly perfect modern mission sections. You are finally given some good answers.\nCons: Terrible map design, over crowding A.I.'s making escaping near impossible. Mission and design logic is deeply flawed leading to some very irratating and facepalm worthy moments.  A.I. behavior switches from irratatingly stupid to that of beyond human reason. (examples: Friendly A.I. killing a target that must be kept alive for mission to succeed. To soldiers instantly identifing you from 100 feet away.) Lots of polish work left undone, bugs and glitches, nothing game breaking just irratating.\nSide Note: I didn't try Multiplayer because I don't like AC Multiplayer in general.\nRank: 3 out of 5 Stars.\nPerson opinion: This is a game for fans of the series and if you can overlook its obvious issues there is a good story to be had, I would recomend the pc version as a cheaper alternative for those interested. It's in between the first game and brotherhood as far as i'm concerned. If you think their is any chance you'll like it it's not bad for the pc price.", "hours": 21.7, "user_id": "76561197983842807", "username": "~Exile~", "products": 146, "early_access": false}
