{"product_id": "208480", "page": 390, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-07", "text": "Although I'm not yet finished with this game, I can already tell that I'm disappointed.  I'm not a huge Assassin's Creed fanboy, but this game really dropped the ball after Revelations gets you so pumped for the next installment.\nThe controls are much too spastic for a big budget title.  Here's a fun game-- try to pick a musket up off of the ground.  Even though there's a prompt in the HUD to pick up the musket, you still find yourself having to hold down the \"F\" key as if you're trying to smother it before the game will actually pick up the musket.\nRemember how fun it was to hop from building to building, assassinating guards on the rooftops in the previous games?  Well, sucks to be you, because the guards (for some reason) have impossibly perfect eyesight in this game!  You might as well have a giant red arrow pointing down at your easy-to-spot head as you stumble from rooftop to rooftop because you'll never get the drop on these guards!  They see me before I see them regardless of the situation-- how is that possible?  I'm supposed to be the life-long trained assassin here!\nI'm barely into this game and it's already stupidly difficult for no reason whatsoever.  I'd definitely pass on this one.", "hours": 26.0, "username": "Your New Stepdad", "products": 922, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 390, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-07", "text": "I would have to say that ACIII probably has the best plot since the original game, and returns to the war of ideals in a much better way than Ezio's plot ever did. It sort of got lost between his snarkyness and trying to be a Renessaince James Bond. Anyway, the characters are memorable, the depictions of the United States' founding fathers are very, very grounded, and the character of Connor is refreshing, shifting from a sarcastic womanizer to an idealistic, strong-willed youngster. It also finally gives a lot more rounding to Desmond's character, and John freaking de Lancie is the VO for his dad.\nLong story short, best game of the series, always worth the cash, pick it up if you love good stealth games.", "hours": 19.1, "user_id": "76561197981568714", "username": "Marcus4600", "products": 311, "early_access": false}
