{"product_id": "208480", "page": 392, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-05", "text": "Half the game is hand-holding pre-scripted linear sequences. The other half is cutscenes. The entire thing is a mess of badly-implemented game mechanics revolving around a character with no personality being inexplicably shoehorned into every major event of the American revolutionary war. Avoid it unless you want to see how a great game like AC:Brotherhood can be made worse in every possible way.", "hours": 34.6, "username": "JimboTCB", "products": 535, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 392, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-04", "text": "If you can slog through the first couple hours...yes i know thats a lot, but once you start being Connor the native american... that hunting is pretty awesome and captaining a boat makes you feel powerful... like your doing the most importantly epic thing in the world. As a side note, the graphics are really nice, I posted some screenshots, which i hardly ever do.", "hours": 83.0, "user_id": "76561197972940198", "username": "Kodiak337", "products": 366, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 392, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-04", "text": "Pros: Delivers the same tried-and-true game play with some new additions, Naval battles are well made and add new flavor to the series.\nCons: Puzzles have been for the most part removed, limited quick-key binds are beginning to show their limitations (Many weapons and items; poor system to quickly access them)\nI think the entire storyline concerning Connor and his predicament made the entire ordeal depressing and futile. I'd rather have played the game from Haytham's perspective; from his beginning and the path he chose.\nMost of the assassin lore has been removed, it was glossed over along with Connor's training, while AC fans might not see this as an inconvenience, newcomers might miss out on the deeper meaning of the conflict.\nStoryline progressions is odd at places, such as being able to liberate forts and hoisting the 13-star flag BEFORE it was introduced to the storyline, along with an important character recognizing Connor without any foreshadowing on how he knew of him.\nOverall it was a decent installment, but doesn't hold a candle to Brotherhood.\nPS. The canoe is a blatant lie.", "hours": 89.2, "username": "Odra", "products": 1239, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 392, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-04", "text": "Great AC game and the story-line is very well done. You get right into it. The graphics are stunning just stunning! BUT there are FPS drops in the cities for most mid-grade Pc's and take a decent computer to run, no question. 7/10", "hours": 43.1, "username": "xxxEvilKlownxxx", "products": 78, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 392, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-04", "text": "The game itself is great... when it runs. On consoles, this game has no trouble, since that is what it was originally developed for. However, on PC, it's a mess. Random crashes everywhere, low performance on great hardware, and of course, the Uplay software. This is the first and last Assassin's Creed I buy for PC. I'm not going to support Ubisoft's lazy and half\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665console ports. By buying this, you're only allowing yourself to be punished with third party software and horrible support. Don't waste the money.\nTL;DR: Great game, horrible console port. Pirate it if you want a version that will actually run halfway decent.", "hours": 46.6, "user_id": "76561198051193897", "username": "Willd\u00f6rness", "products": 93, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 392, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-04", "text": "don't get me wrong, I enjoyed the game, but compared to the other assassin's creeds this one was very disapointing, after playing the 4 hour intro (I am a fast gamer myself and it took me litterary 4 hours) I still didn't get much about all new features, though improvements where made like the freerunning and combat system I felt kinda lost in what to do next, a lot of cool features are gone as well: hiring mercs: gone, shops in every street: gone, that awesome brotherhood of assassins feel: gone. Also the characters are a lot disconnected in the assassin's enviroment. I don't felt like connor or whatever his native name was is a real assassin but more like .... \"native american\". though I still enjoyed playing this it's a thumbs down because It's to low quality for a assassin's creed game", "hours": 43.5, "username": "R34V3r", "products": 708, "early_access": false}
