{"product_id": "208480", "page": 393, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-02", "text": "If it's on sale, especially if it is bundled with the previous Assassin's Creed games, it's well worth it. Tons to do and a big world, but much of it feels empty and pointless. Very unpolished and full of bugs. Characters are forgetable and storyline is mediocre. \"Present-Time\" cutscenes with Desmond are annoying and boring. A dull end to a dull character in Desmond Miles. Regardless of my negative comments it is still fun enough for me to have put over 100 hours into it.", "hours": 111.9, "user_id": "76561198032708813", "username": "Gorpy the Love Bump", "products": 78, "early_access": false}
