{"product_id": "208480", "page": 398, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-29", "text": "Having already being the owner of Assassin's Creed IV Black Flag, I must say that Assassin's Creed III still poses to be a great and unique experience of the American Revolution. What I love most is the interactive and well-blended storyline of the powerful, but naive, Connor Kenway and his journey, tampering with powerful foes, no doubt that this Assassin's Creed deserves an A+.", "hours": 46.4, "user_id": "76561198097910957", "username": "Unorthodox", "products": 395, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 398, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-29", "text": "I waited for a while to finally get this game and I have to say I am thoroughly dissapointed. The game is simply terribly optimized for PC. I may not have a really high end PC but I am able to play most modern games at medium to high setting very smoothly. This game however chugs like a \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665, especially in towns. A look online showed nearly everyone has the same issue. Apparently the code does not properly utilize multi-core processors.\nGameplay is fine, as expcted, but having to play on minimum just to have mediocre performance is unacceptable.\nAnd Ubisoft has the balls to \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 about PC piracy.", "hours": 7.0, "user_id": "76561198017136746", "username": "ramypage", "products": 68, "early_access": false}
