{"product_id": "208480", "page": 398, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-29", "text": "The game looks like\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665and runs like it too, the story is convoluted and stupid. It is not worth 5 dollars, let alone its asking price. Early game mechanics are broken and AI is some of the worst. They can either spot you from across an open area or they will simply stand there when they lose you waiting for death. The introduction to the actual protagonist in the game is frustrating beyond belief, and it mimics the issues in AC1 where you would be chased by infinite enemies the moment the alert was blown. It is really a shame considering revelations weas okay and brotherhood was a masterpiece. Save your money and buy Assassin's Creed 4, it is a much better game with a few bits of sci fi \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665t.", "hours": 9.0, "username": "Lotuseater24", "products": 1077, "early_access": false}
