{"product_id": "208480", "page": 405, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-21", "text": "This is the type of game where you either love it or you hate it. While it does have a very slow start, once the story picks up, you will be on the edge of your seat for the entire time. The controls are a bit different from the previous games, but they are a bit easier to use here. Overall, I rather enjoyd most of the time I spent getting 100% sync", "hours": 81.2, "user_id": "76561198001265352", "username": "Lamiasmile", "products": 378, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 405, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-21", "text": "I really want to like this game. I was a fan of the series and everything in it is fun.\nThe only problem is it's BROKEN.\nThis game is definitely not finished. I'm playing a year after release, and still It's only \"mostly\" finished. Several parts of the game are still obviously malfunctioning. Though there are work-arounds, and it is possible to complete the game, there are things that definitely don't function like you think they would or should. I can tolerate games being a little rough on the edges, but this game needs a sandblasting. If this game were working 100% I'm sure I would love it; except it isn't. Given that over a year has passed, I doubt it ever will be finished.\nWith Revelations being a bit lackluster, and 3 simply not finished, I am definitely not in a rush to play 4.", "hours": 32.2, "user_id": "76561197971253689", "username": "SYYK", "products": 153, "early_access": false}
