{"product_id": "208480", "page": 416, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-11-29", "text": "The main character is insuferable and annoying. The game is playable but the story is a big downturn from the acceptable Assassin's Creed II trilogy. The ship combat is top-notch however and the DLC can also be pretty amusing, but the main game suffers from a terrible main character and a shody story.\nOnly play this if you want to see the end of the Desmond story, you don't need to play this if you just want to jump straight to AC IV.\nBy the way, the game uses two wrappers. Steam and then Uplay. Uplay is awful and will often just lose your save or be down randomly. Ubisoft support is nearly non-existent and very unhelpful.", "hours": 52.5, "username": "Sidotsy", "products": 527, "early_access": false}
