{"product_id": "208480", "page": 422, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-23", "text": "As a big fan of the Assassins' Creed series since the first game, this - in my opinion - just improved on what already was a perfect game, yes there were and still are some bugs but I didn't experience as many as people has claimed there was. The setting for the campaign is good & really enjoyable, again with the Templars seemingly in control and the Assassins on their last legs, only for them to rise up as always and well, you can probably guess what happens. The multi-player is fun & enjoyable also, but for me, nothing will beat Brotherhood's multi-player. Apart from that, it's a game I definitely recommend but then again so is the entire series.", "hours": 21.5, "username": "Isoruku", "products": 512, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 422, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-11-22", "text": "6/10 a great departure from past games\nstory wise:\nit greatly contrast the previous games, it ultimately is a revenge story with no redeeming qualities. past games focus on bringing up of assassins creed and its code, here it's a barebones revenge story, the main protagonist is a selfish child like stubborn person that isn't relatable at all.\ngameplaywise it's really iffy controls. it really feels like a console port and little more. if you HATED the collection part of previous Assassins Creed games, you most likely not like this game, here half of all side missions are collecting/finding things, previous games only had 1 or 2 collecting missions like collecting feathers and treasure chests, here it's\ntreasure chest\nalmanac pages\ntrinkets\nPivots (post game)\nNow that you can hunt:\nhunt/collect:\nanimal X, Y number of times (keep in mind you have to do this in several ares of the game not just one area,) for example, collect 5 deer skins in fontier area A, keep in mind there are other areas so you would be collecting 5 deer skins several times.\nit's kinda sad. this hunting/organic aspect part of the game was tooted as the next step in the series but it just feels sloppy/unecessary. they either needed more time or focused more on the gameplay and story, but in the end you find yourself fast traveling between areas and not bothering traversing the area it's too large and not interesting..\none thing that bug me the most is that you never influenced the world around you. in previous titles you would buy shops, earn money buy property, build up assassins dens and a small army of assassins, the city felt alive/organic, you shaped the city.\nHere, nothing. it feels that you have no influence on the world, there would be a pivotal moment/mission and nothing happens afterwards, the world at the beginning of the game is the same at  the end the game. you actions changed nothing\nREALLY STUPID\nSlight spoiler Alert:\nthe \"Final mission\" is a chase sequence (literally you chase the bad guy), and the story resolves in a cutscene. no fight/battle, a great departure from previous titles where the final was a 3 part series of chasing scenes, sneaking or fights between several enemies or the main antagonist. Again there is no Final fight/battle with the main Antagonist. you feel cheated on the whole experience\nOverall:\nthe game is a clunky console port  with servere gameplay flaws.\nthe story was average at best.\nthey tried their best but it felt like they forced alot of thing from previous titles that didn't work here and added new feature that seemed unecessary or clunky at best.\na collection/completionist fetish really affects gameflow.\nThe game just isn't fun. feels more like you are fighting with it than enjoying it. I wouldn't recommend it to a friend if they wanted to try an AC game i'd recommend AC 2 or Brotherhood.", "hours": 31.5, "user_id": "76561198040843553", "username": "Saint Valentines", "products": 203, "early_access": false}
