{"product_id": "208480", "page": 428, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-10-10", "text": "Since there are so many Assassin's Creed Parts out yet, I'm not sure if this one is worth it, but it's overall a good game.\nI played this game as my first Assassin's Creed game and it surprised me since I just bought it just as a preparation for AC4. It fulfilled its job very good. It's a nice game which may be a bit difficult to controll but if you got it, it can make real fun. The story is a bit more originally then the ones from the new games and it's also a big funfactor.\nIn conclusion I think it's a pretty nice game, which is worth buying when you're a AC fan, if not, I'd prefer trying the newer AC parts.", "hours": 1.8, "username": "GODrums", "products": 725, "early_access": false}
