{"product_id": "208480", "page": 430, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-03", "text": "Best story in a Assassin's Creed game. Some people says that Connor is a emotionless \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 but if you really get into the story you will see Connor's suffering. I literally cried at the some parts and this was the best Assassin's creed with story.\nAnd yeah to be fair, game still haves bugs but really just play it for the story.", "hours": 1.1, "username": "Ataberk Ates", "products": 756, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 430, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-07-30", "text": "In some ways, this may actually be my favourite AC game so far. I can see why it's received all sorts of gentle pummelling from all sides, but it deserves major accolades at the very least for boldly venturing into quite different territory from the previous titles (all too rare in a huge budget sequel!) and actually pulling it off, absolutely superb handling of the historical material and some truly excellent, nuanced and thought-out writing \u2013 though admittedly the protagonist mostly feels like he was written by three different people who didn't quite agree on what they want to do with him. Yes, the feature creep is getting ridiculous, and some of the story missions are much too linear. But it's a splendid experience all the same.", "hours": 61.4, "username": "basilisk", "products": 540, "early_access": false}
