{"product_id": "208480", "page": 438, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-04-06", "text": "Absolument d\u00e9cevant. Cin\u00e9matiques trop nombreuses. On ne joue pratiquement pas dans ce jeu !!! Techniques de combat peu \u00e9volu\u00e9es, tr\u00e8s peu d'\u00e9nigmes secondaires. Ce titre tient plus du documentaire que du jeu. Par contre oui on apprend beaucoup de choses sur la r\u00e9volution am\u00e9ricaine.", "hours": 24.6, "user_id": "76561197971221447", "username": "controlx", "products": 146, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 438, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-04-04", "text": "While not as engaging (and certainly not as addicting) as it's predecessors, Assassin's Creed III provides a great story driven experience that wraps up Desmond's role in the series. The combat system has been tweaked and now seems even more refined, and although I didn't bother much with the side missions, they would deliver endless hours of fun if you're not already \"weathered\" from completing those kinds of quests in previous titles. 7/10", "hours": 21.1, "username": "Jimmy Snakes", "products": 5832, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 438, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-04-03", "text": "Holy crap. If you are any fan of history, especially Revolutionary War history; this game is a MUST buy! Thankfully, the previous entries problems with the user imput has been somewhat repaired, making the controls more intuitive and easy to use. The backstory of the previous games is also somewhat explained for those new to the series, so they can jump right in. Lastly, it has a naval combat system which is very addictive, most likely why the next entry in the series is going to focus on pirates. Overall a very solid game, laced in history.\nI mean, you're basically a ninja slaying redcoats. What's not to like?", "hours": 237.5, "username": "Scott", "products": 436, "early_access": false}
