{"product_id": "208480", "page": 442, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-02-19", "text": "This game!! O M G!! THIS GAME!! I had a great time playing it. Unlike AC1 and AC2 I didn't skip all side quests to get to the end of this game. I savored it. I did every mission. Granted I didn't get all collectables but I don't do that in any game.\nThe ship missions are awesome, the graphics are amazing. The game has so many features and mechanics that just make it immersive. Not all features are a must do sort of thing., You can get by without doing any of the brotherhood stuff or any of the crafting/homestead missions. But If you do it adds great depth to the game.\nThe game is also very dynamic. it changes as the games story  advances. The changing weather is also pretty awesome. The story is odd but I found it to be very entertaining. I can't wait to see where the next game leads. If you got the cash this game is definately worth the money.", "hours": 34.8, "username": "Draul", "products": 4321, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 442, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-02-19", "text": "Assassin's Creed can be vaguely compared to the concept of 'The Matrix' in which you play a protagonist in the 'real world' who becomes someone else inside a 'virtual world'. It tells a fictional story of a war between Assassins and Templars - and spans across several real life historic periods. The franchise is one of few - which tells a massive story back-to-back instead of switching main characters half way through or making massive time jumps. Especially Assassin's Creed III - seems to be the best game in this long standing franchise.", "hours": 38.0, "username": "Vendrium", "products": 819, "early_access": false}
