{"product_id": "208480", "page": 455, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-12-01", "text": "Impressive Game, great Graphics,great Story about the American Civil War.\nThis is definitely the Best Assassins Creed Game.\nOnly that the Tutorial is over 5 Hours long sucks abit , but it's not Boring only abit to long lol\nThe game length is Around 50+ Hours if you do all Sidequest/hunting missions ect.\nSo you get alot for your Money :) If i could rate it , i would give this Game a 9/10.", "hours": 29.1, "username": "DarKshodaN", "products": 2543, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 455, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-12-01", "text": "I like this game a lot, the graphics are really nice and interacting with your environment is what you'd expect from an AC title. I do feel like the story line could have used some more polishing up, the main character seems to straddle the line and never really defines himself as an Assassin. He takes up the code, it seems, only out of a sense of necessity not out of real duty. The ending was a bit weird, but I hope it's just because it's a cliffhanger and that we'll get a proper ending to the series in a future title. This game is fun, but you wouldn't be missing out on much if you waited for it to go down in price.", "hours": 18.0, "username": "Daez", "products": 124, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "208480", "page": 455, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-12-01", "text": "The final chapter of Assassin's Creed saga, what brings it all together? What ties up the pieces of previous games? Find it all here. Travel through 18th century of Civil War as Connor Kenway.a mohawk assassin. Beautiful Graphics and Atmosphere, Average Gameplay, Great Story with some twisted plots, tons of hours will be wasted in this adventure, and it will worth it. Except the final ending of Desmond's story. IT SUCKS, RUINED MY LIFE, FKN HATE IT !!!! 6 out of 10 is my final verdict. If you like naval battles, multiplayer and solid single player as Connor, buy it, if you seeking for best ending ever? look somewhere else. Ending here utterly sucks as much it did in Mass Effect 3", "hours": 42.8, "username": "KuroSun", "products": 615, "early_access": false}
